The rash moved around my body throughout the week: back, torso, legs, arms. Everywhere except for my face and feet. It seemed to be hives, as I would have the urge to itch and then the rash would flare up. This went on from 4/03 to about Friday 4/09 and then it subsided. I was advised by a GP to take Zyrtec twice a day and could use a topical steroid until the rash subsided and to avoid an oral steroid. I have had a handful of rashes throughout my adult life so I could tell this one did not look very serious. Like the standard rash, I was so itchy at night. It felt like my skin was crawling.  I suspect it was my body's delayed reaction to the vaccine shot.

Doctor said it could take up to 4 to 6 weeks to dissipate.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The night after the vaccination, I woke up with extreme anxiety.  I had a week of panic attacks (I am not at all prone to panic attacks - very usual for me), high blood pressure, and a pounding heartbeat with a high heart rate.  On April 7th (two days post vaccine), I developed a vibrating "pins and needles" sensation in my feet and legs, and some transient pins and needles and numbness in my hands and face.  On April 12, I developed a terrible headache in the  back of my head (base of my skull).  There is a squeezing sensation in the back of my head that comes and goes.  I contacted my doctor, and was advised to take antihistamines and advil to try and reduce inflammation. I saw my doctor in person on April 14th, and was given a prescription for Meloxicam, and gabapentin to help calm the nerves.  On April 15th, I visited the ER because the headache had not resolved, even with Meloxicam.  They preformed a Head CT which came back normal, and gave me a shot of Torodol and  antihistamines.  Today, (April 16th), I am finally starting to feel some better, but I still have a mild headache at the base of my skull and some lingering pins and needles sensation.
LAB_DATA: Blood work pending, Head CT normal
OTHER_MEDS: Armour Thyroid 75mg, levothyroxine 75mcg, Fish Oil, Vitamin D, Selenium, Methyl Folate, Iodine, Zinc

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I have not been sick all year.  About 12 hours after the shot, I had a fever, extreme pain and moderate swelling in left arm.  Nausea.  24 hours after vomited.  Extreme fatigue, slept 13 hours straight. 48 hours still fever and fatigue but improving. 72 hours, fever and nausea gone, but still fatigued.    96 hours later felt completely fine. .....   But here is where I find it very strange.  At 120 hours after, my 10 year old daughter develops the exact same systems.   She DID NOT receive any vaccination.  She develop a fever and vomitted approimately according to the same time frame I did.   I find this extremely strange considering we have been very viligant about wearing masks outside our home.    We asked around and we do not know of anyone who has had the flu nor come in contact with someone who had the flu.  I find it extremely bizarre that my whole family has not been sick all year and then 12 hours after I get the vaccine, I get sick and throw up and 4 days later my daughter also gets sick and throws up.    From what I understand, this might just be a bad coincidence, but I felt I needed to report it.  Thank you.

He was discharged on 4/8/21.  On 4/14/21 he presented to the ED with chest pressure/palpitations/dizziness.  He stated that he has had chest pressure for 1 week prior to the this.  CT revealed a saddle pulmonary embolism.  he was admitted to the hospital for further work-up and treatment.
LAB_DATA: ED Course:4/14/2021 20:09:39 -  Patient is a 56-year-old male with a past medical history of hypertension, hyperlipidemia, HIV presenting to the emergency room for evaluation of chest pain, palpitations and lightheadedness described as if he felt like he was going to pass out.  Patient endorses intermittent chest pressure over the last week in the center of the chest which is non-radiating, not worsened by inspiration.  However today patient was attempting to grab something from his fridge and had return of his pain as well as the other symptoms as noted above.  Patient has no recent periods of immobilization or recent surgeries or history of leg swelling.  No infectious symptoms reported.  We will obtain cardiopulmonary labs for further evaluation, D-dimer, TSH.  Will obtain EKG and chest x-ray.  EKG as noted above, chest x-ray is noncontributory. Patient has no leukocytosis, not anemic.  Patient has a mildly elevated creatinine of 1.4 which appears to be patient's baseline with last recorded of 1.2 on 4/8/2021.  Troponin was found to be elevated at 0.046 though with non-ischemic changes on EKG and D-dimer was found to be elevated at 21,173.  CTA was added.  BNP is negative and TSH is within normal limits. ED Course: I have assumed care of the patient from the previous provider who has discussed the clinical presentation, work-up, and ED course thus far.  I have reviewed the patient?s medical record and ED course and agree with all aspects of care thus far.  At the time of sign-out, patient had a markedly elevated D-dimer and was pending results of his CTA. Patient did have mildly elevated first troponin, mildly elevated creatinine 1.4, potassium 5.7 without hyperacute T waves or EKG changes.  Labs were otherwise fairly unremarkable.  Patient CTA ultimately returned showing a saddle embolism.  Given this finding, I will start the patient on heparin.  He is currently hemodynamically stable and does not have any hypoxia.  He is only mildly tachycardic in the low 100s.  On exam, patient does appear comfortable, does not appear short of breath or in acute distress.  I was also able to perform a bedside echocardiogram and did note that he had very mild right heart strain, but still had good squeeze.  Second troponin did come back elevated 0.866.  I contacted the inpatient hospitalist doctor and discussed the patient's presentation with him.  He does accept patient for admission to the stepdown, but is requesting that I speak with ICU.  I did speak with the ICU fellow and discussed the patient's presentation.  He agrees to come down and assessed the patient, but otherwise agrees for stepdown admission.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt presented to clinic for 2nd Moderna Vaccination today. Patient reported to vaccinating RN Hx of anaphylaxis to NSAIDs, Hx of covid infection resulting in multi-week hospitalization in December 2020, reports that she is a "covid long hauler." Additionally, pt reported that she experienced "throat scratchiness/tickle" and "dry throat" immediately following Moderna vaccine dose #1 on 3/16/2021, which resolved after drinking water. Pt was instructed by her physician to bring her personal epi-pen with her when receiving 2nd dose of Moderna. 2nd dose vaccination administered today,with pt agreeing to stay in observation for 30 minutes.  10 minutes post vaccination at 10:24am, Pt reported that she was getting the same scratchy tickle in throat she experienced following 1st dose.  RNs brought pt into clinic room five for closer observation.  10:33am, Pt reported feeling dizzy, was visably shaking, and reported tightening in her chest. At 10:33am, pt was laid down on floormat, and 0.5L Oxygen was administered via mask. 10:35am, HR 77, RR 24, Oxygen was increased to 1.0L. 10:36am, pt reported decreased chest pressure, decreased dizziness, stated "this feels better." 10:40am, pt reported tightness in chest had resolved completely,  denied dizziness, denied itching, however, throat still "tickles." 10:48am, patient remained supine, O2 at 1L, B/P 138/90- pt reports resolved throat itching, states she feels "much better." 10:52am, RNs assisted pt to sitting position, pt states she feels "way better," denied tight chest, dizziness, throat tickle. 10:55am- HR 66, pt given water. 11:00- pt moved to standing position then sitting position in chair, and O2 was removed. 11:10- pt reported breathing and throat feel normal, denied dizziness. 11:16am, pt walked to observation to wait for daughter to pick her up and drive her home. 11:38am, patient's daughter arrived at clinic to drive her home. RN provided education on s/s of anaphylaxis reaction vs expected s/s following vaccination to patient and daughter. RN instructed patient not to drive today and have someone remain with her for at least 4 hours. Instructed not to take benadryl as it may mask symptoms of anaphylaxis. Instructed to go to ED if she experiences difficulty breathing, rapid onset of symptoms such as tight chest, SOB, throat swelling & dizziness. Both patient & daughter verbalized understanding before leaving clinic.
HISTORY: Covid-19 "long-hauler" per pt. Covid Dx on 12/25/2020 resulting in hospitalization for multiple weeks.

5 days after the 1st. Moderna Covid-19 vaccine shot, my left arm started itching that day.  On Friday the itching got worse and the area was sore, when I looked at my arm later that day, my arm had a swollen circle around the injection site about the size of a tangerine.  The area was itching, sore and red.  Saturday morning when I got up the itching and swelling was worse and was very red and hot to the touch and I had developed a rash outside of the circle area.  I called the Drs. office of which they have an acute center on Saturdays.  I was seen about 4:45 pm. that day.  They told me that I had ceullitis (Infection) at the site of the injection on left arm.  They put me on Augmentin for 7 days along with a steroid creme to apply 2x/day for the itching, redness and swelling.   The allergic reaction got to the size of an orange. The medicine was working, by 3 days the swelling and deep redness was gone as well as the heat at that area.  Today is day 6 of being on meds and no swelling, itching, rash or deep red.  You can still see the circular allergic reaction which is still discolored that was about the size of an orange.

Problem # 1: EDEMA (ICD-782.3) (ICD10-R60.9) New onset right scrotal swelling after recent second COVID-19 vaccine. Edema on exam, without tenderness or evidence of torsion. Urinalysis today is negative. Concern for infection is low. We did discuss possibility this could be an immune response to his vaccination. He has no known previous history of epididymitis or orchitis. Our office has recently been made aware there have been documented cases of orchitis or epididymitis in active COVID-19 cases. The data/research in regards to similar symptoms from solely a vaccine is limited/nonexistent as far as we know. Recommended conservative measures including: Allowing time for swelling to go down, regular use of NSAID (ibuprofen or Aleve 23 times daily x2 weeks), ice alternating with heat, and scrotal elevation. Will schedule him for a follow-up visit in 2 weeks to reassess swelling. He will let us know of any new concerning changes in the interim.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Wednesday afternoon, real tired, headache, body aches and chills. Thursday, I was okay. I felt fine and went to work but in the afternoon, I started not feeling too well and my arm was hurting where the injection was and it was very swollen. Friday, 9th,- I went to Urgent Care - the physician assistant said the injection was given too low in the arm. It wasn't in the muscle. It created a rash and cellulitis. I had a big bump on my arm. She told me to wait and see. Friday afternoon I experienced diarrhea and  had that through Monday. Treated it with Imodium on Friday night - (two doses) and one dose on Saturday. On Sunday, I didn't take any. On Monday, I did take one dose of Imodium. From Friday through Sunday I was real sick and couldn't go anywhere and stayed in bed. I couldn't even do a telephone video Dr. visit because I was sick. I went to a different Urgent Care on Monday. He said the injection was a fail. It should have been up in my arm muscle and it was too low in the arm. He said it looked like it might be infected. He prescribed something but said I could wait a day or two first to see if it went away.  I waited for two days first before starting the prescription and I started using the prescription on Wednesday the 14th. My arm is starting to feel a little better today but it's itchy around the bump. He also  said that my diarrhea might have been from a flu virus - he didn't know if it was from the vaccine. The diarrhea went away on Monday, the 12th, if the afternoon.  (Note - They ran out of the vaccine and a new dose of the vaccine was needed to be obtained from Walgreens while I was waiting in line. - when the new batch came they said that this new dose was the same lot number. But Just wanted to note this in case the lot number was different with this batch.)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The day after vaccine administered, I experienced severe fatigue and nausea, which was not unexpected. Two days later, I had a severe headache, especially above my right eye, which was not much reduced with pain reliever (Tylenol). The pain persisted and I saw my long time ophthalmologist on Friday, March 26.  He noted that pressure in my right eye was 44 (approximately 3x normal) and that my cornea in that eye was swollen.  Pressure and vision test for my left eye were normal. I was already taking Latanoprost eye drops, so I was told to continue that.  In addition, he added Brimonidine Tartrate drops and Timolol Laleate drops to my treatment.  I seemed to experience some fatigue after starting drops, which improved after a few days.  However, because Dr. office did not respond to questions I submitted to office about various issues, I decided to seek a second opinion. I first saw second Dr. (information provided above) on March 31.  He agreed with first Dr.'s diagnosis and generally with the treatment, but added a diuretic and substituted Rocklatan for the latanoprost drops I had been on. When I visited Dr., the pressure in my eye had reduced to 34.  I continue on the treatment schedule and do feel much improved.  I am next scheduled to see Dr. on April 27 for follow-up.  Both Drs. do not think the vaccine caused the cornea swelling.  Dr. stated that if it were the vaccine, it would have affected both eyes.  Nonetheless, I am concerned the trauma in my right eye may not be a coincidence.
LAB_DATA: Pressure tests and eye exams performed on March 26 and on March 31.

At approximately 3 PM on 4/5/21, I developed a distinct pain in my lower back, right side. I had not done anything different that day besides getting my shot. It progressively worsened and by approximately 7 PM, I was in great pain while sitting/standing/moving. The pain continued through the next day. I also experienced a mild fatigue that lasted through 4/6. The muscular back pain continued and became debilitating, affecting my daily routine, ability to sit or stand comfortably, pick up my kids, etc.. I began taking half a Tramadol  in the morning just to curb the pain, and alternated ibprofun and naproxen for inflammation. I also regularly use a topical CBD salve for pain relief. The muscles in my lower right back are noticeably harder than those on my left side.  The muscle pain feels like a constant spasm/seized up feeling. I purchased a TENS machine as another pain relief option, and do regular stretches but haven't found anything to take away the pain. It progressed into my right hip, and as of today, 4/16/21, I am still dealing with the muscular pain and hip pain.  Yesterday, on 4/15/21, I woke up with a red rash at the vaccine injection site. It was warm to the touch. I also started feeling ill, shaky/chills/very fatigued, and ended up going back to bed. By about 2 pm, those side effects had resolved and I was left with just the back and hip pain, which I?m still dealing with today.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Typical symptoms began the evening of the day I got the shot (March 21st): sore arm, achy, headache, dizziness, and just generally beginning to feel ?off?. Took Aleve. Symptoms worsened the next day and I was extremely fatigue and that carried into Tuesday.  Taking Advil as needed. Started vertigo exercises ?just in case? to help with the dizziness. By the end of day on Tuesday, all symptoms had cleared except headache, dizziness and fatigue. However, I was beginning to feel a sense of ?brain fog?? I was starting to have a really hard time writing a simple email without it being littered with typos or inconsistent thoughts.  By Thursday I was in my doctor?s office/prescribed meclizine and by Friday he sent me to the ER: EKG, CAT scan and blood work all checked out. No ?real? explanation for my symptoms except a weird reaction to the second shot.   Over the course of the following three weeks, the headache has subsided but flares up from time to time however the ?dizziness?, disorientation, brain fog has continued. Sometimes it feels like I have a focus problem too? like it takes me a while to register what it is I am looking at. Then the more I try to live a ?normal? day, the more I seem to experience something that I refer to as a ?neurological meltdown? starting mid-afternoon and by dinnertime I can barely think my way through dinner preparation. ANY stimulation like children singing, TV noise, dog barking, etc. feels intolerable. It is all I can do to keep myself upright and engaged in the evening routine and then I am passed out on the couch. The other way to describe this is that I feel ?concussive?? like I have a concussion. I have to wear sunglasses now. I can?t listen to music through my headphones anymore? it is just too much for my brain. It is like by the end of the day my ?brain battery? is drained and if I doesn?t recharge overnight, I wake up off and dizzy and just can?t think clearly or remember much of anything.   I saw an ENT on April 12th and am scheduled to see a neurologist on May 3rd. I have NO idea what has happened to me but I was a high energy, multi-tasker, never sit down kind of person who exercised daily until the second shot.  NOTE: Prior to the second shot, I was running 6 miles three times a week and swimming 1 � miles three times a week.
LAB_DATA: EKG, CAT scan and blood work on March 26th in ER: all negative or within normal limits  Saw ENT on April 12th: hearing test revealed compromises to high pitch noises but nothing notable or connected to my presenting symptoms.   Appointment with Neurologist on May 3rd.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patent was given vaccine and started to feel dizzy, light headed, itchy. After resting and fluids for 20 min patient began to feel as if her throat was getting tight. Pt was placed in semi fowlers position and given IM EPI pen in left thigh (10:20) (VS 142/80 HR 74, rr 18) and 1cc IM Benedryl, EMS services were called. At 10:25 (VS 132/82, HR 88, rr 22) pt began shaking, coughing and feeling more "like I cant breath. Repeat IM EPI pen given in rt thigh at 10:39. EMS arrived, report given to EMS staff by physician and nurse. Patient spouse arrived on scene and patient was transferred into ambulance and taken to Health Care center. Only given Allegra for home use.

About 3.5 days after my second pfizer dose (dose was given April 12, this happened around 1:30 am April 16) I awoke with extreme vertigo. It felt as if the room was violently shaking. This also caused me to break into a cold sweat and become very nauseous. The extreme shaking subsided after about 1 minute but I continued to feel dizzy and unable to stand for another few minutes.   After about 20 minutes the dizziness and nausea had subsided enough that I was finally able to fall back to sleep and woke up hours later with a headache and feeling a little shaky, but no longer dizzy.  For what it's worth I have had this reaction one other time in my life--15 years ago when I took mefloquin for malaria, it triggered vertigo. I switched to a different malarial prophylaxis and have never experienced vertigo again until this week following the second pfizer dose.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had been hospitalized 3-4 times between 2007 and 2009 for cellulitis on my face originating from my outer ears. No particular cause was found at those times. I was just hospitalized for the same problem (first time since those previous episodes) on April 14, 2021. Condition has been diagnosed as Relapsing Polychondritis, a rare autoimmune disease affecting the cartilage of the body. Now, the question is: Is it just coincidence this flare occurred after getting the COVID vaccines, or did the vaccine somehow stir up my immune system causing it to bring on this latest episode?
LAB_DATA: Standard blood work, cultures, and tests required for hospital admission.
OTHER_MEDS: Singulair Crestor Senna Plus Effexor XR Tradjenta Protonix Estradiol Progesterone SR Synthroid Vitamin D3 Flonase Calcium + Mg 50+ Women's Multi Vitamin Nystatin Ointment Albuterol

PT RECEIVED HIS COVID-19 VACCINE AND WAS WAITING IN THE OBSERVATION AREA.  AFTER ABOUT 10 MIN MY TECHNICIAN NOTICED HIM SIT ON THE FLOOR FROM HIS CHAIR AND SHE CAME TO GET ME.  AS I APPROACED HIM HE LOOKED DAZED AND SUDDENLY BLACKED OUT.  IN ABOUT 15-20 SECONDS HE AWOKE AND ABOUT 1 MINUTE LATER HE WAS SPEAKING.  ROUGHLY 5 MINUTES LATER, EMS ARRIVED AND CHECKED HIS VITALS, BLOOD SUGAR AND EKG.  ALL WERE WITHIN NORMAL LIMITS.  WHILE TALKING TO PATIENT AND THE TWO LADIES WITH HIM, WE FOUND OUT HE HAD DRIVEN 3 HOURS FROM HIS HOME TO COME TO OUR PHARMACY FOR THEM TO GET VACCINATED.  AND THEY PLANNED TO GET ON THE ROAD AND RETURN.  EMS SUGGESTED HE GO TO THE HOSPITAL, BUT AFTER 20 MINUTES HE WAS WALING AND TALKING AND DRINKING WATER.  HE AND HIS FRIENDS DECIDED THEY WOULD NOT GO TO THE HOSPITAL.  I FOLLOWED UP WITH HIM 2 DAYS LATER ON  4/9 AND HE FELT FINE EXCEPT FOR SORENESS AT THE SITE OF INJECTION.  HE ALSO RECALLED A TIME WHEN HE HAD PASSED OUT FROM AN INJECTION WHEN HE WAS A TEENAGER
LAB_DATA: EKG, BLOOD SUGAR, BLOOD PRESSURE AND PULSE
OTHER_MEDS: PT TOLD EMS HE TAKES A BETA-BLOCKER (HE THOUGHT METOPROLOL)
PRIOR_VAX: AS A TEENAGER, HE FAINTED AFTER A VACCINE

I had the second shot at the same place on 2-11-21. At the time, I only had soreness of the left arm at the injection site and virtually no other symptoms except a mild headache for a few hours.  However, during the month or so between the vaccines and post-vaccine period, I developed pain in both shoulders with moderate-severe rotator cuff symptoms. This was pain in reaching in almost any direction. Also, I began to notice heaviness in both upper legs, front and back, which in a week or so progressed to tiredness and then to achiness, and finally to pain when I would squat, bend over, or get up from a chair. I have  never had either symptom before.
LAB_DATA: Orthopedic consult, XRays, and ultrasound showed some microtears in bicpes and supraspinatus tendons bilaterally and minor arthritis in the right shoulder joint (on the head of the humerus). Using ultrasound, a steroid was injected into the right shoulder. The next day, all symptoms were gone. They came back except the most severe right shoulder pain in about 3-7 days. After another week, I was prescribed 20 mg/day of Prednisone for a week and then 10 mg/day for another week. Most of the shoulder and leg symptoms were gone during that time. They returned three days after going off the Prednisone. This started with chicken and then progressed to beef, pork, any meat. A week later it progressed to where garlic started to taste bad. Meat and Garlic have the same rancid smell to them. It then progressed to my bowel movements smelling the same way. Then progressed to always having the bad taste in the back of my mouth. About 2-3 weeks ago tap water started to smell very strongly of chemicals.  Now it has progressed to Meat, Garlic, onions, or anything in garlic family, strawberries, zucchini, peanut butter, chemical smell of water, coffee, and then just foods here and there that do not taste terrible but do not taste good either. The only foods that taste completely normal are sweets like icecream or cake. My diet is now consisting of protein bars, protein shakes, salads, chips, cheese, and sweets. It?s been challenging especially since garlic is put in 90% of all food products it feels like. If I open the container of garlic powder it can make me gag until I vomit if I smell it long enough. I did mention this to my Primary Care Doctor. She stated that she would be willing to refer me to a specialist if my symptoms persist into June or so. Patient was pre-screened for vaccine eligibility and determined to be eligible, however, was placed in the 30 minute observation group due to history of severe allergic reactions. Once the 30 minutes was up, patient left clinic and got into her car. She noticed redness/rash/possible hives forming on her face, neck, upper neck and upper arms when she got in her car. Patient returned to clinic and notified staff she thought she may be having an allergic reaction. Medical personnel examined her and decided to call 911 for additional resources and a more thorough assessment. Patient stated she felt like her chest was tight and was visibly upset. Once clinic staff informed her the ambulance was on the way, patient stated she thought chest tightness may be related to anxiety about what was happening. She said this looked similar to other allergic reactions she had that developed into something more serious. Patient used both of her inhalers. Ambulance arrived and did an assessment and concluded patient was having an allergic reaction, however, her oxygen saturation was 100% and patient was talking normally so Paramedic did not believe her breathing was compromised. Rash/redness remained localized to areas described above. Patient lived about an hour from the clinic site and was informed closest hospital was 45 minutes away with intermittent periods of no cell service, medical staff recommended ambulance transport. Patient really did not want to go by ambulance because she stated she "felt ok" but acknowledged the risk of driving herself that far of a distance and possibly not being able to call for help - she did agree to go by ambulance. Patient was transported without incident in approximately 15 minutes of the ambulance arriving.
LAB_DATA: Follow-up from ambulance crew - patient was treated with diphenhydramine and Zofran (anti-nausea) in route to the hospital and felt like her symptoms had pretty much entirely resolved by the time they arrived at the ED (~45 minutes after leaving scene).
HISTORY: Patient stated she had a history of severe allergic reactions, and moderate-severe asthma

I will begin by noting that I am known for high pain tolerance and have been a strong, healthy, professional athlete for thirty years. The evening of the vaccination, I went to bed at 9pm feeling odd. By midnight, I became paralyzed with excruciating pain throughout my torso and arms with such an extreme fever that it felt as if my heart was going to stop. I had crushing chest pain which inhibiting my breathing ability in a way that could only be compared to being crushed under a burning truck. The paralyzation was so intense, with pre-existing pain multiplied by a thousand, that I couldn't even speak to alert my husband, who was right beside me. This continued for several hours until it subsided enough for me to pass out from exhaustion. The following day I battled residual aches throughout my torso and arms, accompanied by a mild fever. The trauma of fearing for my life that night and over the past week, exacerbated by the news of this vaccine I received being paused for issues related to my demographic, had made me too afraid to report my extreme side effects until now. With the encouragement and support of my family, I have worked up the courage to do so. It was the scariest, most intense pain and fever I have ever experienced in my life all at once and no one I have described this to has ever heard of the severity of what happened to me.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am not sure if my event was caused by the vaccine I received on  April 8, but I have a very strong feeling it is, as never in my life have I experienced anything like it.  My day began normally, and I just had returned home from an appointment.  I had some lunch, and a few minutes later as I was standing in my kitchen,  I began sweating terribly,  heart was racing, and I felt like I was going to pass out.  I  managed to make it to a large living room chair, and once I say down and put my head back, I passed out.   My daughter witnessed everything and said when I passed out, my arms were trembling and my eyes rolled back.  This lasted for about 30 seconds.  She was unable to arouse me for a bit, but when I came to my speech was slurred.   I did not know what had happened.  My daughter called 911.  By the time medics arrived, I was feeling much better and aware of everything happening.  The checked for signs of stroke, vital signs, blood sugar, and everything was normal.   I was transported to the ER, and my work up there was normal, including EKG and blood work.  The physician that I saw diagnosed me with  vasovagal syncope and did not feel the event was related to the vaccine.  I  completely recovered, and like I said  I?m not sure if it was related to the vaccine I received or not.  I just feel that it may be worth noting since I?ve never had an experience like this and  I?m pretty healthy with really no medical history.
LAB_DATA: EKG and blood work in ED.

Patient admitted 4/14/2021 to the ICU from ED.  Patient was experiencing hand weakness.  Patient given TPA as treatment for a potential stroke.  Patient with known stroke on CT imaging, unable to further verify with MRI imaging.  Upon further investigation/discussion with the patient, he reports receiving the Johnson & Johnson Vaccine 10 days prior to admission.  Patient with known comorbidities which increase his risk of an embolitic stroke however with recent findings from the CDC, unsure if this needs to be further investigated.  Patient had 2 head CT scans, showing no intracranial abnormalities and MRI was unable to be completed due to patient's size. Neurology states high probability of stroke within their consult note. Patient's risk factors for stroke include: uncontrolled hyperlipidemia (LDL 132 on Crestor 40 mg daily PTA), hypertension (as high as 182/92 mmHg in ED), physical inactivity (BMI 76 kg/m^2), and male. Low suspicion of CVST based on patient's platelet count of 212 on admission and no abnormality on head CT. MRI would have been beneficial in potentially diagnosing CVST, as well.   Our recommendation is to submit this information to the VAERS database as a possible ADR from the vaccine. The patient fits the timing of an ADR, within 6-13 days of vaccine administration, and CDC recommends watching for neurological symptoms based on their most recent press release.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within an hour of receiving the vaccine, I began to feel "odd" (i.e heart racing, spine tingling, strange sensations in my hands, and dizziness).  At the hour mark, while trying to "walk it off" inside my backyard, things escalated quickly.  As I came back inside, I suddenly collapsed and and lost consciousness.  Luckily my best friend was with me and she described my behavior as a full on seizure (which I am not predisposed to).  According to her, I was flopping around, spitting wildly and drooling all over my face, my eyes wide and glazed staring into nothing, lips turning blue.  She immediately called 911 and within 5-10 minutes, two EMT's arrived and began to speak to me and take my vitals.  For a good 15 minutes I couldn't sit up and had to lay on the ground, still extremely out of it - unable to think, merely in extreme discomfort similar to the most intense flu I've ever experienced.  After a half hour or so, I sat up and was able to thank them for helping me and answer some of their questions.  Over another 15 or so minutes they said all my vitals were perfect and they were not worried about me - sure I'd make a full recovery, which I hope I did.  I am feeling MUCH better today.  The reason I felt it so important to submit this report is because I had never heard of anyone experiencing side-effects that severe.  Of course I had heard it could wipe you out, give you chills, aches, and exhaustion - but I had never heard that it could lead to a seizure so scary that my best friend thought I might be dying.  I truly don't know what might have happened without her.  People should know to have someone at home with them after the second dose.  I am not over-exaggerating about my symptoms whatsoever.  My body still hurts all over and I feel as if I went through some type of gauntlet yesterday.  I absolutely do NOT want to discourage anyone from getting the vaccine, but I wish I had some notion that something so severe could happen to me.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 71- year old woman with past medical significant for hypertension on 10 mg of Lisinopril daily for many years. She had her first dose of Pfizer vaccine two weeks prior to admission (3/11/21). After her vaccination, patient felt unwell and dizzy in the mornings. She felt persistent fatigue and had a decreased appetite. The week prior to admission she noticed a decrease in her urine output. She denied NSAID use. Her primary care physician ordered blood week and her Cr was found to be 16.54 and BUN of 163, phosphate of 17.5. Her last known Cr prior to her admission was 18 months prior and was 1.17. She was asked to present to the emergency room. Renal ultrasound showed no hydronephrosis or stones. Urinalysis showed 1+ protein, spec grav of 1.023 with a urine protein/creatinine ratio of 0.09. Urine sediment was unremarkable. Her temperature was 95.6 and her BP was as low as 75/46 and she was put on a low dose of levo. CRP was 202.3. COVID was negative. CK wnl.  ANA + to 1:160 (dsDNA, Smith, RNP, SS-A, SS-B all negative). Blood smear was negative. Cultures were all negative. Echo showed an EF of 68% with trivial pericardial effusion. Patient was oliguric, and then initiated on hemodialysis. Renal biopsy was performed.   The biopsy consists of one fragment which is stained with H&E, PAS, Trichrome, Jones Silver, and HPS stains. Review of all stains reveals 12 glomeruli, one of which is globally sclerotic. The architecture of the kidney is well-preserved. There is  interstitial fibrosis with proportional atrophy involving 10% of the biopsy tissue. There is a focal interstitial infiltrate consisting of lymphocytes involving <5% of the interstitium. The tubules show diffuse acute tubular injury.  Calcium oxalate  crystals are present in seven tubular profiles. The glomeruli show expansion of Bowman's capsule. The mesangium shows normal cellularity. The vessels show no abnormalities.   IMMUNOFLUORESCENCE MICROSCOPY:   Frozen sections are stained for IgA, IgG, IgM, C3, C1q, kappa, lambda, and fibrinogen. All immunofluorescence stains are negative.   ELECTRON MICROSCOPY:   Specimens are prepared for electron microscopy and semi-thin sections stained with toluidine blue are reviewed prior to thin sectioning for ultrastructural examination. Electron microscopy demonstrates patent capillary loops. The glomerular architecture  demonstrates segmental corrugation of basement membranes with increase in lamina rara interna.  No subepithelial deposits and no intramembranous deposits are identified. The tubules show dilated mitochondria and injury. There is segmental effacement of  foot processes. There are no subendothelial deposits. Mesangial electron dense deposits are not identified.   Patient received three dialysis treatments and Creatinine began to improved down to 1.46 within 8 days.
OTHER_MEDS: Lisinopril, tumeric, aspirin, co-enzyme q, chondroitin, pyridoxine, omega 3

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my second shot for COVID-19 on March 1, 2021 at approximately 11:00.  I had no reaction until 2:00 am March 2, 2021.  At that time I was experienced severe pain throughout my body, joints, muscles, etc.  When I attempted to get up I was barely able to move without assistance.  This continued for 3 days.  I returned to work after the 4th day but was still experiencing severe pain throughout my body, especially my joints.  At that time my husband contacted the virus hotline and was told that what I was experiencing was normal and not to worry it will go away in a few days or possibly a couple of weeks.  It has now been a month and a half since I received the second shot and this past week, I experienced symptoms as severe as I had the first 3-4 days after receiving the injection.  My doctor has given several test and ordered several more in an attempt to determine what is causing the problem.  My doctor prescribed a medication for neuropathy that has helped with the pain slightly somewhat.  I am also constantly tired, my blood pressure and heart rate are also elevated  which may be caused by the pain I am experiencing.  Prior to my second shot, the only medical problem I had was my blood pressure has been elevated since I moved to a higher elevation, but this was completely controlled with one amlodipine a day.  Other than that my last physical my blood work showed absolutely nothing to be concerned about.  As a matter of fact, almost all of my levels were text book perfect.  I have always been very active and healthy.  This vaccine is the only thing that I have had or changed that could have affected my health so negatively.
ALLERGIES: None that I am aware of.

I stayed in observation at the CVS pharmacy for about an hour before leaving.  I felt normal and thought it was over.  About 20 mins onto the interstate the burning sensation went over my whole body.  I also experienced a tingling in the back of my head.  I also got dizzy and felt very faint.  This episode lasted for about 20mins before calming.  I felt normal again for a 2-3 mins and it would happen again where I felt dizzy and faint.  This occurred multiple times in waves.  I called the paramedics and they recommended I take another dose of liquid Benadryl. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Shortly after my first dose of Moderna on 3/13, I experienced a constant ringing in both ears, very noticeable during the daytime and when trying to sleep. I also experienced some dizziness / mild vertigo that still comes and goes. After my second dose on 4/13, the ringing has become much louder, so I did research and learned this is a common side effect. I also have pulsating / throbbing in both ears. I had no other side effects with dose #1, but experienced extreme chills, aches and fever (101.3) for two days following dose #2. Both my husband and son had two doses of the Pfizer vaccine and had none of these side effects (good for them, unlucky for me!).
LAB_DATA: While I am hoping the ringing will stop or at least minimize, I do plan to go to my ENT to check it out; although it sounds like nothing can be done about it given it's from this vaccine.
HISTORY: I have had chronic tinnitus for the last 20  years, but could only hear the ringing at night when sleeping, and was very low/tolerable. Shortly after my first dose of Moderna on 3/13, it got much louder and was noticeable during the daytime! I first thought it was just my condition suddenly worsening. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 18 hours after the shot, I had a near syncope event. My arms and legs became weak and heavy. My limbs still have not recovered their strength. I cannot be left alone because of near syncope events and I cannot stand long enough to make food or shower by myself.  I have had 6 more near syncope events, two of which landed me in the ER. About a week after the shot, I developed moderate vertigo with nausea and a worsening of tinnitus in my right ear. The tinnitus has returned to normal as of today, so far. The vertigo is decreasing slowly.  I am still nauseous, especially first thing in the morning. I still have limb weakness and shaking. The intensity waxes and wains. I check my blood pressure multiple times a day, especially when feeling light headed or faint.  Most of the time it is in 100-115/ 60- 90.  The worst near syncope episodes were 102/56 and 108/60, respectively. Blood sugars within normal range. Oxygen between 97-99% and pulse between 80-95 bpm.   Currently, I am on a 30-day event monitor for my heart. My doctor has prescribed a low blood pressure medication, 2.5 mg of midodrone, but haven?t taken it out of fear.
LAB_DATA: All blood work, CT and X-rays have come back normal on each occasion.
HISTORY: Hashimoto?s Disease and PCOS and allergies and vasospasms of the eye
ALLERGIES: Aspirin, Penicillin, Sulfas, Cipro, Vicodin, Codine, Amytriptoline, Zoloft.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient came in for first Covid shot. After the vaccination, he was instructed to stay for 15 minutes in the "post vaccination" area. He went and sat there and I walked back into the pharmacy to finish the paperwork. I then was alerted by a customer that the patient fell off the chair and hit his head. I ran over to him and by then, he was back in his chair and just realized that he had passed out. While I was with him and talking with him, we paged out for code white. I had instructed one of my techs to call 911 as he was pale and palms were sweaty. I had him walk over to the IMZ area and had him lay on some towels and had his feet propped up on a chair. He was given water and I kept talking with him until EMS arrived. They checked his vitals and were asking standard questions and after about 15-20 mins, he was feeling better and didn't want to go to ER. By then, his coloring was much better and he stated he was feeling a lot better. I asked him if he had a headache and he says that he didn't have a headache and was more embarrassed than anything. He thanked me for my professionalism and care and assured me that he felt back to normal. I called him 2 hours later and he was doing well.

Took benadryl, went away in two days.   For the following 7 - 10 days, I had EXTREME JOINT PAIN, FATIGUE AND MALAISE.  Went to my family doc - no fever, no cough, no headache.  Doc felt the immune response from the Vaccine may have thrown me into an RA/Fibro Flare.  Prescribed mobic and muscle relaxer for joint pain.   On Day 10 after the vaccine, I developed a HUGE STYE in my left eye., being treated with antibiotic eye ointment. I am now 16 days out from the 2nd Moderna dose and am finally starting to feel human again. I hope I am on the Upswing now.  Fatigue is diminishing along with extreme joint pain.
HISTORY: Hashimoto's thyroiditis, Seronegative Rheumatoid Arthritis (no medication take for RA except mobic and muscle relaxer if needed for pain),  Fibromyalgia,  Breast Cancer Survivor (no meds taken), Treated 2018 w/ chemo and surgery, Anxiety
PRIOR_VAX: Pnemovaxx 23, August of 2017
ALLERGIES: Pnemovaxx 23 vaccine, Seasonal allergies, pollen and dander, nitrous oxide,  morphine, compazine

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt has hx of vasovagal reaction when getting any sort of immunization/injection. Pt found in Vaccination boot number 1 with healthcare provider. PT had just received his Pfizer immunization. PT stated he wasn't feeling well and needed a moment. Pt then became diaphoretic, pale, cool skins. Paramedic asked patient if we could take him to cot for observation. PT agreed and stood up turned and sat in wheel chair.  PT taken to cot and as we arrived pt became unconscious. Pt was unresponsive to verbal and painful stimuli. Pt remained unconscious for approximately 20 seconds. Once patient regained consciousness he was immediately Alert and Oriented x4, skins were pale, moist, cool. pt was carried to cot during his unconscious episode. pt layed down for a while, vitals were assessed at 1556: BP-128/88, HR 64, RR 22, SPO2- 94%. Pt immediately feeling much better and taken to observation for an additional 30 minutes. Pt advised to let us know if he was feeling faint again.
Menstrual cycle began 4 days early, was heavier and lasted longer.  No treatment necessary.  Normally very regular to the day. This has never happened before.
Headache, muscle aches, diarrhea the following day and one week later.  Soreness and discoloration at injection site the following day to date.

This was his first time receiving Hep A vaccine; he had received doses of the other two vaccines before at his previous well checks.  Afternoon of shots he was very calm and weirdly still when awake. During his 2 naps he slept more than usual.  Evening of shots he had thrown up in his bed some point over night (he sleeps from 7p-7a so not sure when in course). On Tuesday (shot was on Monday morning) he had no appetite. Would barely touch food or liquids. Again slept more than usual for naps. Threw up around 5pm the small amount of food he had eaten. Overnight he had diarrhea.. he woke up in middle of night upset and I changed him, his clothes, and bedding. By morning he had more diarrhea in diaper.  Wednesday still no change in appetite. Still diarrhea that I was having to either bathe him after or change entire clothes and sheets. Was up in middle of night upset again with diarrhea. (Mind you; he has been sleeping through the night from 7p-7a since almost 3 months old with no problem unless sick).  Thursday I am concerned for dehydration. I leave a message for nurse on call to help me diagnose symptoms of dehydration. I ask if this could be vaccine related and she said no most likely not - because it had lasted. (Side note: we have a toddler and two adults in the household as well who have still yet to get the said virus). His lips have been cherry red I guess from either not drinking enough or not feeling well.  Thursday night he woke up inconsolable. When I picked him up it was as if he didn?t realize I was there to comfort him and was just crying nearly inconsolably. I realized more diarrhea and changed everything. Got him some milk and got him calm and down.  Friday still no change. A little more appetite at dinner but then quickly out of blue was inconsolably crying for over 30 mins. I tried bathing, singing, toys, walking outside, etc all thE tricks but wouldn?t ?snap out?. Only had one pee diaper today and still diarrhea.  Increasingly more irritable to no avail.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient came in excited to get his first moderna covid vaccine. Got his dose at around 1230pm and was instructed to sit down for 15 minute post -vaccine to make sure he felt ok before leaving.  About 10-15 minutes later, he came up to the cashiers and his face was pressed against the plyglass and started to go down.  (RPH) and (tech) ran out to catch him from falling to the ground.  We pulled a chair up to where he was so he could sit down.  He reported to be warm, weak, and dizzy.  He remained seated but was alert.  He has no allergies, no medical conditions, no prior reactions to vaccinations.  He last ate at 8:30am.  He said he felt warm, but I took his temp again and it was 96.7 degrees.  We gave him some water and he remained seated.  After several minutes, he was able to get up and was fine with moving his chair away from the front registers and towards the side wall (within sight of pharmacy).  Kept checking on him and he was getting better and better.  He did call his friend to pick him up instead of driving home himself.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Uncontrollable shaking for roughly 1-hour and 20-minutes. Convulsive as though extreme hypothermic, patient could not control it. I said I felt cold, even though I had a fever that was extremely high (no thermometer to measure) my wife then put the 30lb weighted blanket on me and after about 15-minutes the shaking started to decrease before finally subsiding completely. I then had a drink of water at room temperature which lowered my internal core body temperature and slight shaking started again until I warmed back up and stopped. Our house was 73 degrees F which normally I would sleep in my underwear, instead I was fully dressed, under all our blankets plus the 30lb weighted blanket and I still felt cold.  That night I had sweated more than ever, my pillow was literally a swamp and stayed damp until the next night although pillow cases were removed. Half of the king size bed was soaking wet and yet I still felt cold.  I sweated through the sheets again for 2 more nights before my body finally started regulating its temperature again and have since been okay. Felt very lethargic for 5-days.

The night after the vaccination I developed a mild fever (under 100 F) and had a severe headache.  It lasted most of the night.  When I got up in the morning, both symptoms were gone and I assumed I made it through any side affects.  That whole day I felt great.  I had delayed my daily 7 mile run, which I normally do in the morning, to make sure the symptoms were really over.  So by 4 pm, still feeling great, I decided to go for that run.  I didn't run particularly hard or fast,  It was a relaxing, enjoyable run.  No issues.  When I got back home around 5:30 pm, I went straight back to my office to keep working.  I was feeling hot, as you would expect after a run, so I turned on the ceiling fan.  after about 15 minutes I started to feel like I was shivering from the cold, so I turned off the fan.  Within less than 5 minutes, I was shacking and my muscles were spasming uncontrollably.  It was similar to the couple of times in my life where I have gone into shock from an injury.  So I dropped everything and made my way as quick as I could to a very hot shower.  I was scared enough to ask my 17 year old daughter to check on me to make sure I don't pass out.  A couple time I thought about calling 911, but I didn't have my phone and I was afraid to leave the shower.  After about 20 minutes in the near scolding shower, I stopped shaking enough to where I decided to wrap up and get under a bunch of covers laying on the bed.  The shacking  completely stopped after 5 or 10 minutes in bed, but the fever shot up and I developed a debilitating headache.  I took Tylenol and eventually Excedrin Migraine to ease the pain.  The fevered stayed over 100 F most of the night (my normal temperature is a little above 97), and the headache remained but gradually declined.  By 7 am the this morning I was fine and I've been fine all day.  The only reasons I'm reporting this is because the shaking was very severe, at times I wondered if I was heading for a seizure, and, being a runner, I want to make sure there is not a link between severe reactions and distance running shortly after the vaccination.
HISTORY: Exercise induced asthma (at very high levels of effort - patient is a distance runner)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Primary side effect that I experienced is swelling and tenderness in my left armpit and collarbone, which onset 24 hours after the vaccine injection. After about three days, the swelling and tenderness had expanded to both armpits, the entire collarbone area, neck and throat (difficulty swallowing). It's been four days now and still experiencing side effect, which hasn't subsided.  I also experienced muscle pain, joint stiffness (especially in neck and shoulder), fever/chills and fatigue for the first 24 hours.

Right after injection had slight tingling in my arm all the way down to my fingers in the right arm, the arm they gave injection in.  My arm was sore that day, but nothing too severe.  The next morning I woke up and felt like someone had hit me multiple times with a baseball bat in my right arm.  It was very sore and hurt to move.  I also noticed that my legs seemed very stiff and my walking was more difficult.  I have multiple sclerosis and do have mobility issues.  I have been doing physical therapy for the past 6 months and getting stronger and my walking was getting better.  Ever since my first vaccine, I have noticed greater difficulty with my gait and increased spasticity in my legs, and heightened lack of energy.  My physical therapist has also noticed the changes and the direct correlation between my decline and the date of Moderna vaccination.  I have chosen not to get the second one because the symptoms were so severe and lasting.  MS is a disease that affects the immune system.  It is like my immune system mounted a response to the vaccine and has never calmed down since then.  My walking is definitely worse than prior to the vaccine!!
OTHER_MEDS: Setratline, Synthroid, Amypyra, Mybetriq, Vitamin D
PRIOR_VAX: small pox at 18 months of age

I administered a Pfizer COVID19 shot to the patient as a first dose. I then had the patient go to the post vaccination waiting area to wait for the 15 minute post vaccination period. At about 7.5 minutes into the 15 minute time frame the patient approached the consultation window complaining of tightness in her throat and jawline, numbness and tingling in her face, and feeling faint. I administered 20ml of 12.5mg/5ml liquid diphenhydramine for a total of 50mg of oral liquid diphenhydramine. The patient then stated that the tingling was progressing to her extremities. I then administered 0.3mg epinephrine auto-injection to the outer aspect of the right thigh at 11:02am. 911 was called and a code white paged through the store. The patient continued to experience tightness in her throat and tingling and stated that it was worsening at 11:08am a second 0.3mg epinephrine auto-injection dose was administered to the outer aspect of her left thigh. Paramedics arrived on the scene at 11:09am and the patient was taken to the hospital. Patient remained responsive throughout.

When checking out after the 15 minute wait time, patient said she didn't feel very well and fell down hitting her head on the pharmacy counter.  When she came to, she said she felt "weird",  lightheaded and clammy.  We offered her a drink of water and before she could take a drink, she passed out cold. She was out for about 20 seconds and then came to again and we took her down to 1 layer on top and gave her a bag of ice while waiting for the ambulance to arrive.  She was treated/observed by the ambulance crew and after another 15 minutes, agreed she was good to go home with her 2 friends that she had ridden with to get her vaccine.
LAB_DATA: Ambulance crew performed blood pressure, pulse and temperature.  (4/16/21)

The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.    Purpuric Rash and Thrombocytopenia After the mRNA-1273 (Moderna) COVID-19 Vaccine. Cureus. 2021;13:4     Previously administered products included for Viral hepatitis C: Interferon. Concurrent medical conditions included Viral hepatitis C, Chronic kidney disease (Stage 4, with a baseline creatinine of 3 mg/dl.), Uncontrolled hypertension, Systolic heart failure (Ejection fraction of 35%.) and Liver cirrhosis.    On an unknown date, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) 1 dosage form. On an unknown date, the patient experienced RASH (Generalized non-itchy, non-painful rash a day after receiving the vaccine) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), THROMBOCYTOPENIA (Thrombocytopenia) (seriousness criteria hospitalization prolonged and medically significant), PURPURA (Purpuric rash) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), ACCELERATED HYPERTENSION (Accelerated hypertension) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), ACUTE LEFT VENTRICULAR FAILURE (Systolic congestive heart failure exacerbation) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), NAUSEA (nausea) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), DIARRHOEA (few loose stools), PYREXIA (Fever) and CHILLS (Chills). The patient was hospitalized for 3 days due to ACCELERATED HYPERTENSION, ACUTE LEFT VENTRICULAR FAILURE, NAUSEA, PURPURA, RASH and THROMBOCYTOPENIA. At the time of the report, RASH (Generalized non-itchy, non-painful rash a day after receiving the vaccine), THROMBOCYTOPENIA (Thrombocytopenia), PURPURA (Purpuric rash), ACCELERATED HYPERTENSION (Accelerated hypertension), ACUTE LEFT VENTRICULAR FAILURE (Systolic congestive heart failure exacerbation), NAUSEA (nausea), DIARRHOEA (few loose stools) and CHILLS (Chills) outcome was unknown and PYREXIA (Fever) had resolved. On unknown date, during the observation post vaccination, the patient opened the window to the car for air, reported to the nurse that she felt dizzy. The nurse practicioner arrived to the car with emergency supply cart. Patient was reclined in the passenger seat and stated she felt weird and felt. The patient then slumped down and appeared to have lost consciousness for a few seconds. The patient was breathing and began to shivery significantly. Blood pressure within normal limits, she was tachycardic with elevated respirations. At 1237, the nurse practicioner administered 0.3 milligrams intramuscular through the patient's jeans into the right thigh. Patient tolerated it well. I will not be getting a second dose of ANY Covid-19 vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I started getting a headache about an hour along with pain in the back of my neck and a mild headache after my shot (maybe an hour or so).  Around 1100 hours, about the time I got back from the Facility, I began to feel a tightness in my throat and got a little raspy.  When I drank water and ate a little, it hurt similar a hangover as if dehydrated, but went away after a minute or so. About 1400 hours began to develop chills, causing me to get into bed, and then the chills, overall muscular pains, very tired, moderate headache and some nausea ensued as well along with an initial low grade fever.    Fever went up to 102.1 degrees and had fever till about 2130 hours and broken only after I took two (1) Tylenols. Still had a very low grade fever till about 2300 hours or so (99-100), but finally went away.    I awoke next day (13 APR) about 0800 feeling a bit better, but with a moderate headache and touch of diarrhea.  Headache lasted all day.  This prompted me to contact my treatment facility and a telecall was conducted giving them my symptoms.  They recommended Rizatriptan should my headache continue and Tylenol not enough to relieve.  I cannot take any analgesics due to my liver disease and Thrombocytopenia.  Finally  my headache went away (with a slight hint it might come back), but no more fever, chills etc.    On 14 APR, no more headache but still felt a little tired.  From 15 APR through today (16 APR), no further symptoms and feel great, but prepared to report anything that may develop laer.
OTHER_MEDS: MVI (MULTIVITAMIN) ORAL TAB PANTOPRAZOLE hydroCHLOROthiazide 25 MG ORAL TAB Fluticason Propionate (Flonaise) Olapatadine

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Vertigo; Blood pressure 195/130; Extreme weakness; Passed out; Pain in the base of neck/Pain in brainstem area of neck; Ear fullness; Pain entire right side of brain/head; Disoriented; dizziness; Off balance; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS (Passed out), VERTIGO (Vertigo), HYPERTENSION (Blood pressure 195/130) and ASTHENIA (Extreme weakness) in a 52-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 041L20A) for COVID-19 immunization. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     The patient's past medical history included No adverse event (Patient reported no acute or chronic illnesses and no allergies.). Concomitant products included VITAMIN D3 from 10-Jan-2021 to 07-Feb-2021 for an unknown indication.    On 29-Jan-2021 at 12:00 PM, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 01-Feb-2021, the patient experienced BALANCE DISORDER (Off balance). On 01-Feb-2021 at 10:00 AM, the patient experienced DIZZINESS (dizziness). On 08-Feb-2021, the patient experienced LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS (Passed out) (seriousness criteria hospitalization and medically significant), ASTHENIA (Extreme weakness) (seriousness criterion hospitalization) and DISORIENTATION (Disoriented). On 08-Feb-2021 at 4:00 AM, the patient experienced VERTIGO (Vertigo) (seriousness criterion hospitalization) and HYPERTENSION (Blood pressure 195/130) (seriousness criterion hospitalization). On an unknown date, the patient experienced NECK PAIN (Pain in the base of neck/Pain in brainstem area of neck), EAR DISCOMFORT (Ear fullness) and HEADACHE (Pain entire right side of brain/head). The patient was hospitalized from 08-Feb-2021 to 11-Feb-2021 due to ASTHENIA and VERTIGO, then on 08-Feb-2021 due to HYPERTENSION and LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS. On 08-Feb-2021, LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS (Passed out) had resolved. At the time of the report, VERTIGO (Vertigo), HYPERTENSION (Blood pressure 195/130), ASTHENIA (Extreme weakness), DIZZINESS (dizziness), NECK PAIN (Pain in the base of neck/Pain in brainstem area of neck), EAR DISCOMFORT (Ear fullness), BALANCE DISORDER (Off balance), DISORIENTATION (Disoriented) and HEADACHE (Pain entire right side of brain/head) had not resolved. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Severe 8/10 chills, body aches, pain in the joints especially in the extremities.  Came on 24 hrs. after dosing.  Severe (and I mean severe and painful) for 2 hrs+ then started coming in waves and now intermittent.   Other mild to moderate - fatigue, pain in arm at vaccination site, axillary lymph node is 3 x 2 cm on vaccine side, cough, mucous production, headache.   Only reason I didn't go to ER is coworker (also in health related field) and neighbor had experienced similar severe chills, joint pain, body aches but their symptoms also included fever of 101 to 103 for 3 days.  Had I not known about that, I would have gone to the ER because I would have thought I was sick.  This was worse than when I had influenza with pneumonia a few years back.

Received COVID-19 vaccine within  2 hours of non-OB transvaginal radiology appointment, follow-up appt related to finding from prior hospitalization for sepsis and pyelonephritis in late November 2020. Menstrual period did not formally begin/return(?) until April 12. Experienced heavy flow going into the 5th day now, expect period to end soon as cycle normally lasts no more than 5-7 days. Suspect radiology and/or vaccine could be cause for delayed period.

Pt admitted to the ICU on 3/22/21 w/ pleuritic chest pain and shock requiring vasopressors. At time of admission pt had been taking antibiotics for an upper respiratory infection for 3 days. Echo Lv 40-45% upon admission. Pt was determined to have myopericarditis. On 3/24/21 pt was transferred to the cardiac intermediate unit. Endocrine consulted while in the cardiac intermediate unit to control his elevated blood sugars- endocrine team unable to determine if blood sugar is type 1 or type 2. on 3/27/21 pt went into respiratory distress required bipap & high flow nasal cannula and had a fever. Pulmonary consulted at this time- determined to be related to pulmonary edema and not a PE positive for pleural effusion. ID has been negative up to this point. 4/9/21 pt transferred to internal medicine service for work up for fever of unknown origin and continued management. Rheumatology consulted for leukocytosis, anemia, and elevated IgG. Ruled out connective tissue disease, stills disease, and vasculitis. Histoplasma was borderline positive pt has had recent bat exposure. Bone marrow biopsy done on 4/13/2021, ruled out HLH. Bronch done 4/15 to assess for TB, histoplasma, negative results so far. As of 4/15 no recommendations from ID and patient continues to look weaker/fatigued and spikes fever.

patient was doing well as outpatient with no significant issues post-allogeneic hematopoietic cell transplant.  Received 1st Moderna COVID19 vaccine on 2/3/2021. Found to have biopsy proven lymphocytic interstitial pneumonitis with diffuse alveolar damage/ARDS requiring supplemental oxygen.  Started on systemic steroids without response.  Also with concurrent mild transaminitis.  From prior recent labs, LFTs were normal prior to presentation with hypoxia.
LAB_DATA: 3/24/21 - COVID nasal swab negative CT chest 3/24/21 - bilateral diffuse ground glass opacities bronchoscopy with EBUS 3/26/21 - interstitial pneumonitis, all infectious work up negative 3/29/21 - started on 1 mg/kg/day of prednisone 3/31/2021 - added azithromycin 250 mg per day 4/6/2021 - repeat CT chest shows progression of underlying process Week of 4/6/21 - evaluation for chronic GVHD, including transplant exam, ophthalmological exam, dental exam, dermatologic exam - no findings of chronic GVHD; PET-CT scan overall unremarkable except for likely inflammatory FDG uptake - no evidence of lymphoma relapse 4/12/2021 - repeat CT chest shows stable findings compared to 4/6/21, PFTs show FEV1 of 39% predicted, unable to complete diffusion capacity testing 4/13/21 - VATS with biopsy of right upper, right middle, and right lower lung lobes.  improvement in interstitial inflammation, no evidence of BOS or organizing pneumonia 4/14/21 - progressive worsening of lung disease with increased oxygen requirement 4/15/21 - transferred to ICU for extreme hypoxia and high-flow nasal cannula 4/16/21 - CT chest shows worsening lung disease, no PE, no signs of new infectious process; given 1 gram of methylprednisolone
HISTORY: ALK-negative anaplastic large cell lymphoma requiring allogeneic hematopoietic cell transplantation on 10/19/2020 without ongoing complications, no GVHD, good immune reconstitution, no signs of lymphoma, no active infectious issues.  Chronically HIV+, Hep B+ - compliant with antiretroviral therapy that included antiviral for Hep B reactivation prophylaxis.

On the day after vaccination I had extreme dizziness and faintheadedness, and heavy brain fog. I could not drive or stand up for long periods of time. I was having issues expressing thoughts and having my normal conversations. This was accompanied by strong headache on right side of my head and slightly stuffed sinuses. The day afterwards all symptoms disappeared. However, they reappeared at milder levels intermittently through the next several days. I am now at day 14 with the dizziness and brain fog still occurring intermittently and last night had short episode of abdominal pain. I decided to call the doctor's office this morning when the dizziness started again, for advice and to schedule a brief exam. They told me to go straight to the ER instead, so I went and had blood drawn. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 39 y.o. male with no significant past medical history who came to the ED with a sudden onset of chest pain that radiated initially to his right shoulder then to his left shoulder, left arm and back with intensity of 7/10 starting Tuesday 4/13/21 associated with sob that is worse when laying flat or taking a deep breath   States he received his second Pfizer vaccine on Sunday, 4/11/2021 at 11 AM and started experiencing fever, chills, headaches, body aches and uncomfortable around 11 PM. He finally decided to take Tylenol x2 on Monday between 2 PM and 11 PM with some relief.  He felt a little better on Tuesday morning and did some work from home but later around 7 PM, he notes a temp of 100.2, experienced body aches which he attributes to Vaccine side effects because his wife was also not feeling well post Vaccine. He went to bed and woke up later with cold sweats, felt pain in his chest and back. He described his chest pain as constant pain/heaviness that "felt like someone is sitting on his chest", he later felt pain in his left arm and back prompting ED evaluation.  He denies similar episodes in the past, denies abdominal complaints, denies lightheadedness or dizziness, palpitations, shortness of breath at rest, orthopnea, PND, syncope, denies urinary complaints, denies smoking, drinks alcohol socially.  States his father has CAD and MI x2 with stent in his 50s, his mother is doing okay with no cardiac history.   In the emergency room, his EKG is consistent with pericarditis, initial troponin noted as 4.24 with repeat noted at 8.91, his LFTs are elevated at 107/123.  He received full dose aspirin, Lopressor 25 mg with improvement in pain.  IMG cardiology is on board with plan for cardiac cath today by doctor.  Echocardiogram showed EF of 35-40% with wall motion abnormalities with initial reading.

This is a medication error report. Several final doses were drawn from the final vial near the end of the clinic.The final dose draw was an insufficient dose of 0.4 ml and set aside for disposal. It was subsequently inadvertently co-mingled with the other full doses and administered. This was discovered after at least 5 people were vaccinated and brought to  my attention. Immediate review could not determine an exact recipient. Review of information from moderna regarding dosing errors indicate that antibody response in the trials were comparable for both the 50mg and the 100mg doses studied and that an error producing between a 50 and 100mg dose should not be repeated.

On March 13th, 2021 I was given the opportunity to receive the Janssen Johnson & Johnson Covid 19 vaccine so I decided to go ahead and get vaccinated.  Within 1.5 hours of receiving the vaccine, I began to feel unwell. It started with my left leg going numb. From there symptoms continued to increase. I got very tired could hardly stay awake. Then the chills hit. I could not get warm.  By the next morning (Sunday day 2) I had developed a low fever, headache, body aches and whole body weakness. I could still hardly stay awake still. When I was awake, I was very dizzy and I felt like everything around me was moving but I was not. My left leg still felt numb but I thought it would pass on its own.. Because of how I felt, I just laid around and rested. My injection site was swollen, Red and extremely hot to touch.  Next comes Monday (day 3), I got up that morning, still not feeling well. I made my way to work. That did not go well. The more I moved, the worse I felt. I was completely unbalanced and looked like I was drunk. I couldn't walk straight, I had to randomly grab onto chairs and sit down. I was feeling weaker by the minute. I left work at that point and went to see my primary physician that afternoon. At this point I could see straight to drive myself, could hardly walk as my left leg now dragged. I had no balance and having lots of dizzy spells at this point. He suggested I head to th ER but eventually decided we could wait until morning to see if things improved at all. If no improvement,  I was to go to ER. Tuesday Morning (day 4), my husband took me to the emergency room. I had reached the point of not being able to walk unassisted. At this point, the weakness and numbness I had on my left, had spread to my right side. We had no idea what was happening. We got right in and discussed what was going on. What lead up to me being there, etc. The ER ran blood work, xrays of my chest and 3 different MRIs trying to figure out if something happened like a stroke. NOTHING was present on any test they did yet there was something obviously wrong with me. My arm was still very Red and hot.. I had developed a lump in my arm where the vaccine was given. After ruling out everything the doctor could think of, he consulted with the on call neurologist since it was obvious to him something was happening with my neurological system. The diagnosis...my body was taking the vaccine as a toxin causing my neurological system to react and shut down. They felt that I should be starting feel better in the next few days as the vaccine settles into my system. I was told to follow up with a neurologist and my primary. I was then discharged from the hospital in the condition I had arrived.  Wednesday (day 5) I spent the day at home, not able to do anything. I napped most of the day. I still felt like crap and had no idea when I would start feeling better. No improvement that day.  Thursday (day 6) I woke up feeling a bit better. My right side was beginning to feel normal again but I was still feeling weak and unbalanced. This is also the day I meet with a neurologist to follow up. I don't know that this appointment had accomplished much as she didn't have access to all my medical records. She ended up prescribing me a medication to help with nerve pain I was having in my left side and referred me to do physical therapy. I am to follow up in 2 months.  Friday (day 7) my right side is back to pre-vaccine stage. My left is not. I feel pretty good except the occasional dizzy spell and the fact my left isn't working yet.  Day 8 and beyond...I'm feeling ok. I went back to work but still have issues with my left side and residual dizzy spells. I began physical therapy 2 days a week to work on strengthening my left side however it has yet to help.  I am now just over 4 weeks post covid vaccine. I am now using a cane to help me walk as my left side has still not returned to normal. It is unknown if it will. I'm in Physical therapy 2x a week still. The lump at injection site is now the size of a pea. I still have moments of unbalanced feeling and dizzy spells.
Extremely heavy period.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Presyncope occurred the morning after receiving the vaccine. I did not actually faint, but when I got out of bed in the morning and walked across the house I suddenly had ringing in ears, started sweating profusely, felt lightheaded and felt like I was going to faint. This lasted for at least a couple minutes.   I'd received the vaccine at 9:10am on 4/14. The first side effects started around 8:15pm and were along the lines of what I expected: body aches, low fever, fatigue, chills. Overnight, despite the fatigue, I had trouble sleeping due to heart palpitations and intermittently feeling too hot or too cold, and eventually I had a headache. All night, I was falling asleep and waking up a little while later.  At around 6:30am on 4/15, after sleeping poorly, my headache had gotten bad enough that I decided to take acetaminophen. I had not previously taken any medicine leading up to the vaccine or after getting the shot. I got out of bed and walked across the house, and that's when the presyncope came. Feeling very faint, I sat down, took the acetaminophen, and waited for the feeling to pass.   Once the feeling did pass, I started to feel better pretty quickly, which may have been the medicine working, and then I was able to sleep for a few hours. A slight fever came back over the course of the day, I took a couple more small doses of acetaminophen as needed, and then on 4/16 I woke up feeling fine.

I experienced chills, which intensified in the evening into full body shudders before finally calming. Alongside this, I felt extremely sore, especially in the joints and feet, like they had or were being pressed or squeezed. This made it hard to move around or get out of bed. I had similar symptoms after my first shot, but while those symptoms were still noticeable and took me out of work, I had a much stronger reaction this time around. SYMPTOM_TEXT: 15 hours after my first dose of Pfizer Covid vaccine I had intense uterine pain. My arm also hurt a lot (tho that did not worry me as "injection site pain" is listed everywhere as a "common" side effect). I couldn't sleep because the pain in my abdomen was so strong; I finally fell asleep at 3 a.m. .. and when I woke up at 6 a.m. I was perfectly fine - no pain at all, not even my arm (!) Zero pain. Then 4 days later I got my period. Getting my period was notable because my last period prior to this was 5 months ago. I am reporting because nowhere are these side effects listed as possible so I was pretty scared. I have since heard anecdotes from people having similar side effects and so in case you are planning to update "possible side effects" I wanted to make sure to add my story, in case it could help someone in the future. Side Note: your website  warnings about false reporting are jarring and inappropriate. It is too bad that you believe so many people are planning to somehow sabotage this reporting system. Maybe it is necessary. But it sure didn't make me want to report my side effects. Thank you for reading my "report" ~

he evening of 3-4-21 when I got home from work, I ate dinner, then started shivering badly with temp of 100.5.  The shivering quickly changed to more of a convulsing and temp got up to 104.7F.  When I woke the next morning, temp was back down to 101-102F and most of shakes were subsiding.  But I noticed that I had a deep, cutaneous pain reaction from head to toe when I awoke on 3-5-21.  I could not brush my hair because my scalp was too tender.  I couldn't let anything touch me and put pressure against any part of my body.  Then at 3:30 that afternoon, I went to bathroom and had a bowel movement.  It was so excruciating that I truly though my colon might have come partially out.  I was in too much pain to flush, so I crawled across the house to my bed and laid on my side for an hour, crying.  When I was finally able to go back to the bathroom to flush, I was expecting a large BM.  It was not.  It was about 2" x 1" and soft.  There was no blood.  It just felt like it tore me up.   ****Then at 7:30 PM on 3-5-21 was when things got very serious.  I was sitting down watching TV after a light meal.  Suddenly, I started noticing discomfort deep in my upper back, between my shoulder blades.  Within 5 minutes, it was at its worst....I was have rated it 11/10 pain.  The pain was just very deep, behind the spine, about palm sized radius and unrelenting.  My first thought was "maybe this is musculoskeletal since I've been in bed a lot because of the pain today."  So I looked in my medicine cabinet for what I had and took 5 mg of Oxycodone and 10 mg of Cyclobenzaprine.  An hour later, these meds hadn't touched it.  I was beginning to really worry about an MI, or aortic dissection or pulmonary embolism (though I had no SOB).  Lying flat on my back on a hard surface seemed to provide the only relief (though minimal relief, 9/10 pain).  I called another provider who was on call and told her.  She said that I could try taking 800 mg of Ibuprofen, but if I wasn't relieved in 1 hour, I needed to call 911 or have someone take me to the ER.  I was asleep in an hour.  I took it easy the next two days but started feeling back to normal during the days.  I continued to sweat throughout the nights and skin pain continued so much that I had to cut some of my hair out.  That following Tuesday, the deep upper back pain returned.

I am awaiting Cardiology consult 4-28-21 to see if anything can be done.  The pain I continue to feel is apparently the aneurysm  :0(

On 2/26/21, a consult was placed for hospice care and he was accepted for hospice care at a contract nursing home. Upon review of scanned records, it appears he had a stroke/intercranial hemorrhage on 2/10/21 and that is why he was admitted to the nursing home for skilled nursing services. A date of death of 3/18/21 is recorded. No autopsy results recorded. 38 days from vaccine #2 and date of death.

death  Narrative: Patient received Moderna covid vaccine #1 on 1/22/21 and #2 on 2/24/21. On 3/4/21, he was admitted to a facility for shortness of breath x 1 week. SYMPTOM_TEXT: chest pain, muscle spasms, pain in leg, Narrative: This is a 50-year-old female with history of hypertension, obesity, diabetes who received first dose of Moderna Covid-19 vaccine on 3/26/21 around 1:37 pm. Within 24 hours, the patient reported episodes of shooting pain to her left upper chest and left arm then radiated to left leg and calf area. She also had headaches and elevated blood pressure. The patient did not report the event until 4/10/21. She was evaluated at the Emergency Department (ED) on 4/10/21 for atypical chest pain/arm pain. She was sent out on hydrocortisone 2.5% cream, baclofen for muscle pain, and meloxicam for pain. On 4/14/21, patient returned to ED as she was still experiencing multiple episodes of left sided chest pain radiating down to the left arm. Patient had nuclear stress test which was negative for any reversible cardiac etiology. Pt had mri and mrv which were both wnl. Her lisinopril dose increased and pt's bps are now well controlled. As of 4/16/21, patient reported that she still has lingering left arm pain but symptoms much improve. She was discharged home in stable condition on 4/16/21.
