Rash continued to get worse until about 4 days after the vaccination. At this point I sought treatment at a local urgent care. The urgent care personnel said they believed the rash symptoms were caused by the Modern COVID-19 vaccination, did not identify any other possible causes, and encouraged me to report it to the VAERS system. The treatment followed was topical 1% hydrocortisone cream applied to the affected areas, and 12.5 mg of diphenhydramine taken orally before bed. The rash symptoms improved with treatment but have not fully resolved at 5 days after the vaccination.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: It started with a sorr arm and fatigue. The problem began after I was lying down in bed for 1 hr and 1/2. I laid down at 3:30am, but at 5am I was still awake and my left arm felt like it had fallen asleep. The problem was, I could not seem to wake it up. When I turned on my flashlight, I found that nearly all of the veins in my left hand were invisible, actually everything past the elbow on that side. I tried for about 10 mins while lying down to get blood flow back, but nothing was working. My face.felt very warm and the rest of my body felt very cold. When I finally got up to turn on my bedroom light, I found that all of my veins from my chest down were almost entirely invisible as well. I normally have very visible and easy to get blood from veins (except sometimes in my right arm), so this was very worrying to me. I got up and paced a little around my room to try and get blood flowing again, and I felt pretty shaky while doing this. My hands and feet would shake when I held them up. After about 5 minutes, I sat down on my bed because I did not feel well standing anymore, and I waited. Maybe 10 minutes later and things seem to be returning back to normal. I am still very tired but my whole body seems to have blood again. I am also currently on day 3 of my monthly cycle, but this has never happened in relation to that either.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Short Summary: DVT followed by Multiple Bilateral Pulmonary Embolisms (significant blood clots in both lungs). Context: After the first vaccine (about a week before my second vaccine), I self diagnosed myself with a calf injury due to extreme pain in my calf that felt like a continuous cramp. The extreme pain lasted until my second shot (about a week). When going for my second shot, I reported a rash with hives on my lower abdomen that had appeared within five hours of my first shot, so they requested I stay a little longer for observation. That night I began having some breathing difficulties, but assumed they were to be expected. The breathing difficulties continued to get worse until my nurse practitioner told me to go directly to the nearest ER (2/16/21), where I was officially diagnosed with multiple bilateral pulmonary embolisms. I was admitted to healthcare facility for 24-48 hours, until an EKG revealed heart abnormalities that caused them to use a physician's transport to move me to another unit. I was discharged from the hospital on 2/2/21 after I stabilized from heparin shots, avoiding more invasive procedures. I have been in ongoing recovery since then, receiving ongoing care from a hematologist and pulmonologist. A little extra context for you - I arrived to the hospital with diabetic ketoacidosis and have an endocrinologist since hospitalization that has diagnosed me with Type 1 Diabetes (previously misdiagnosed as type 2 - I'm now on insulin which is controlling my blood glucose well).
LAB_DATA: So many done in the hospital repeatedly - ask hematologist for records or contact me for records if needed
HISTORY: Diabetes (diagnosed as type 1 after this event occurred, previously misdiagnosed as type 2), Hashimoto's Disease

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 51 year old female with chief complaint of dizziness.  Approximately 10 minutes post vaccine administration, patient stood up in and approached the observation staff.  The patient was asked if she was okay and did not respond but grabbed the table to stop herself from falling.  The patient was immediately assisted to the gurney in and placed in a supine position.  Vital signs obtained and initial vitals signs stable.  Patients legs elevated.  Patient was A&O x 4 but was slow to respond to questions.  The patient complained of dizziness and denied any other complaint.  The patient never lost consciousness and there was no traumatic event.   Patients second set of vitals signs demonstrated a decrease in blood pressure and paramedics were contacted.  Patient had a molar extraction by her dentist x1 week ago and denied any other medical history.  Allergies to PCN and only medication is Advil/Ibuprofen for tooth extraction.  Patients husband confirmed medical history and information.  Patient had equal grips/pushes with no facial droop, arm drift or slurred speech.  Paramedics arrived, received report and took over patient care.  Paramedics placed patient on cardiac monitor showing a normal sinus rhythm.  Blood glucose normal with pupils equal and reactive to light.  3rd set of vitals signs returned to normal and patient stated that she had a significant decrease in symptoms.  EMS explained risks and consequences patient but denied further evaluation, treatment or transport with EMS.  The patient was wheeled to private vehicle and was transported by husband home.
LAB_DATA: Vital Signs and stroke test.  Paramedics performed cardiac monitoring and blood glucose found to be within normal limits.
CUR_ILL: Patient had a molar pulled by dentist x1 week ago.

Patient a 46 yo female with a history of Bechet's presenting to the ED yesterday due to a history of progressive bruising with later appearance of petechiae and gum bleeding.   CBC yesterday revealed an isolated thrombocytopenia with platelets of 19k (>340k all previous checks), suspected ITP.  She was given 1 unit of platelets, solumedrol x 1 and IVIG.  Platelets this morning have responded but more likely related to the platelet transfusion.    Today I discussed continuation of IVIG and transitioning over to pulse dexamethasone 40 mg x 4 days q 14 days for 4 cycles in order to put the ITP in remission.   Considerations for precipitating event leading to the ITP include autoimmune condition recently undergoing dose adjustment, history of recent infection (viral gastroenteritis), and post Covid 19 vaccination induced ITP-currently described incidence between 1 in 100,000 to 1 in 1,000,000 and seen between 1-3 wks after vaccination.     This is unlikely to be related to vaccine induced thrombotic thrombocytopenia (VITT) as there is no sign of clotting.  In addition she received an mRNA vaccine (Moderna) which has not been reported to cause VITT. A HIT antibody was sent.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 48 hours after injection, a 2-inch red, warm rash started on my left arm at the injection site. It was warm, slighly itchy, and very painful and swollen. It hurt enough that I couldn't sleep on my left side for several days. By the third day after injection, the rash had grown considerably, but the pain was less. Now 17 days later, I still have a dark pink and almost grey, oval shaped patch of skin on my arm that's approximately 2.25 inches wide and 1 inch high. It's no longer in pain, though the area is still slightly warm to the touch, and tender like a healing bruise. I also experienced two days of extreme fatigue three days after the injection. I had the injection on the afternoon on Thursday, April 1, and by Saturday, April 3 I had terrible headaches and felt complete wiped of energy. This lasted until mid-day Monday when I started to feel better. My husband, who also received the same Pfizer vaccine (same lot number and time/date of injection), did not get a rash, and only experienced the 'punched in the arm' pain on the arm for a couple of days. He also reported some fatigue.
OTHER_MEDS: Pantoprazole; Triamterene HTZ; Allegra; Equate/Generic Excendrine Migraine
PRIOR_VAX: Arm pain and swelling from tetnus shot as a child. No other reactions
ALLERGIES: Codeine; Lyrica; Cymbalta; Mango; Artificial Sweeteners

SYMPTOM_TEXT: According to the dr, my nerves are likely inflamed. Symptoms are feeling of numbness but no loss of circulation. Most often feelings of cold in random parts of my body but especially my left leg (same side as injection). Both sensations appear to only be that because to the touch nothing is colder and to the eye nothing appears cold (blue). This started Friday 04/09 and was initially tingling in my left leg and quickly changed to feeling cold. (Interestingly the day I was vaccinated a few hours later I felt what I thought was the vaccine go through this same leg) Since Friday the cold feelings have randomly been in both both legs, both arms and both hands, less often in my face (left side mainly) and the top of my head. It?s not everywhere simultaneously but sometimes different places at one. Sometimes it can actually associated with being a little cold, but other times with no cause. Regardless it?s an exaggerated cold feeling. First it was like ice cold water being poured into whatever spot it was. It?s now less icy but still cold. Very strange
LAB_DATA: None yet but scheduling stuff this week

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Three hours after injection, I began to feel flu symptom (weak, fatigue, achy, chills, sweats, all-around unwell.)  Six hours post injection, flu symptoms  worsened along with explosive headache.  Nine hours post injection, severe sensitivity and pain with any contact along with burning sensation of entire body.  Pain felt in extremities.  Twenty-four hours post injection, symptoms continued along with excruciating, sharp stabbing pain of shoulder, shoulder blade, wrist, hand of injection arm.  The pain has almost caused me to pass out.  NSAIDs nor acetaminophen  has decreased discomfort or excruciating pain.  Heat nor ice pack has made any improvement.  My skin has felt extremely hot to the touch but I have not had a fever.  It is now over seventy-two hours since receiving the injection.  The pain continues to be unbearable.  The pain I am experiencing in my arm/shoulder/wrist/hand/shoulder blade is unbearable.  I would rather risk contracting COVID-19, then experiencing these side effects again.
OTHER_MEDS: levothyroxine, Vitamin C, Vitamin D3, multivitamin

I am scheduled for my second shot next week but will likely not get it, for fear of making the tinnitus worse than it already is.  I can barely put up with it now, if it gets any worse after the 2nd dose I will greatly regret getting the 2nd dose, so I am likely to skip it.
LAB_DATA: No medical tests, but I did discuss with my PCP, he noted another one of his patients complained about the same tinnitus side effect.  He cautioned against getting the second shot, as I am a healthy 50-year old male.  1st dose gives 80%+ effectiveness, so I am not willing to trade a few more percentage points of immunity for a lifetime of ear ringing.

Around 5:00-5:30 PM (about 2 to 2.5 hours after the vaccination), I started to feel a bit tired.  I took Tylenol, beginning around 5:00 PM.   By 8:00, I was feeling tired enough that I went to bed early.  By 9:00, I had terrible chills and body aches throughout my body.   The aches were worse in my chest / torso -- maybe from so much shaking.  I did not watch any of the men's championship game that night.  I also felt nauseous but I seemed to lack the strength to vomit.  I can not remember a time when I had so much physical pain in my life.  My hands felt numb / tingling.  I tried to drink some ginger ale but drinking was difficult.  Although I was aware that I was breathing and my heart was beating, I thought that I might die.  The terrible pain continued for a few hours.  Around 10:30 PM, the pain dissipated.  However, after about 10 minutes of relief, the pain returned, perhaps worse than before.  At around 11:30, my wife came to bed.  She suggested that I try relaxing Yoga breathing.   I did that and the pain stopped and I fell asleep.   The next day, I woke up with a typical headache and took more Tylenol.  I continued to improve the remainder of the day.
CUR_ILL: No illness.  I received shingles vaccine at most recent appointment with primary care doctor.  That appointment was roughly 6 weeks earlier.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: A fairly aggressive visual migraine, Episode lasted 15-30 minutes almost exactly 24 hours after injection.  It would seem there was no mention of migraines as a side affect. This was unusual as normally they normally  do not interrupt my vision greatly and are simply in my vision and usually only in one eye. In this case it wasn't limited to one eye or one spot.. there were multiple and made it hard to focus and see. Usually when I get visual migraines, a headache comes shortly after. So far as of this writing, I only feel a tinge of a migraine coming on, but it is seeming to fade already.  Should note, I do not get migraines often (maybe once every other year or so.. ) and when I do it is usually after extended exposure to the sun and not on a chilly morning when I first wake up. Thus this report.

I had continued chest pressure and some numbness on my left side in my arm, leg and later my face. No home remedies worked and rarely do I get back/neck/shoulder pain. I was not doing anything strenuous. I went to the ER where they tested me for blood clots (J&J news had just come out and I have a family history) and prescribed valium for the muscle tension which has somewhat helped.   I fully recognize that this might be bad luck, a series of unfortunate events after I received my shot.  However, I have not been sick all year, I have never had acid reflux issues or pain like this in my neck/back/shoulders previously.  The fact that in the 4 weeks after the shot I have not had a single day where I felt normal is a red flag to me. I feel like it is worth reporting in case anyone else has had a similar experience.
LAB_DATA: Initial "viral" issues: Covid test and Strep test on 3/22-prescribed Nystatin for mouth and told to wait it out Diagnosis of acid reflux, possibly resulting from viral infection was from 3/28-prescribed pepcid 20mg 2x a day Visited Urgent Care for back pain/chest pressure-they recommended a trip to the ER to check for clots (news had come out previous day) to be safe, though they reassured me it was unlikely.  My family history is what I think really prompted them to recommend this route.   ER-they ran all kinds of blood work, chest x-rays, a CT scan of my head and neck, EKG.  Everything was normal, my platelets were robust and no signs of clots.  Prescribed Valium to help lesson the muscle spasms.  This is where I am at now and will follow up with my PCP next week.
OTHER_MEDS: Allegra, Seasonale, daily multi-vitamin, Elderberry, Zinc, Vitamin C, probiotic, bi-weekly allergy shots
ALLERGIES: Augmentin-causes severe stomach discomfort Steriod Injection-tried for carpal tunnel, nearly passed out No food, all other allergies are pollen/dust related

The patient is a 29-year-old adult male with severe intellectual/developmental disabilities, is Deaf and blind, and doesn't communicate with words. Since oral sedation was unavailable at the time of vaccination, extra precaution was needed to ensure that he was calm and relaxed before administration. Various distracting techniques were used, and being in his own environment mitigated stress that he might have experienced had he been in an unknown facility. Unfortunately, due to the nature of how quick the dose needed to be administered before he noticed that something was wrong, only about three fourths of the dosage (0.5 ML) was administered, possibly around 0.3 or 0.4. The provider is going to attempt to compensate for this in the second dose series after they are able to order an oral sedative from his primary care provider. I received the vaccine around 11am and did not experience any adverse reactions aside from a sore arm throughout the day.  I went to sleep at 10pm and was awakened at 3am with moderate soreness in my arm and I began to feel feverish and woozy.  About 2 minutes later I could tell that I was going to faint.  The thing I remember was waking up on the floor next to my bed with my wife holding me up.  She said that I started making sudden, loud guttural noises and she was afraid that I had been choking.  She reached over to touch my arm and my body jerked out of bed and I hit the ground.  When I woke up, I realized that I had fainted (I have passed out after a flu shot a couple years ago, but that incident happened about 15 minutes after injection) and my entire body was trembling and sweating profusely.  My wife left the bedroom to get me some water and a cold towel.  I got myself back into bed and passed out again.  The trembling and sweating continued but gradually decreased for about 15 minutes until I felt back to normal.  After I had calmed down, I felt no adverse symptoms and fell back asleep and have felt fine since the incident.
PRIOR_VAX: Flu shot in 2018, I fainted 20 minutes after injection

Woke  up the next morning Monday April 12, 2021 at 4:40 am with the room spinning. I have had Vertigo in the past, as a matter of fact I had got Vertigo so bad when I myself got COVID-19 back in November 2020. My head was spinning all day and then I ended up getting  a terrible headache. I took Tylenol & Dramamine and helped a little but still had a slight headache with Vertigo.  The next day I called my doctor because still woke up with Vertigo and a slight headache, saw him Tuesday April 13th and he worked on me and felt better the next day. Woke up Thursday April 15th with still some symptoms and still having slight headache & Vertigo.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt safety incident post 1st Moderna vaccine At 1258 shortly after administration of Moderna vaccine #1  while in the post vaccine observation area Pt stated she was dizzy and hot (room was very warm) BP was taken 163/95 p68 (AT HOME RUNS 110s/60s, p 70-80) Oxygen 98% RA Pt feeling like she was going to faint and stated throat feels tight.  Remarked in normal sentences she has a vocal cord d/o and gets easily  winded and SOB, not on any inhalers. Pt uses CPAP with oxygen at night at home. Pt placed in a manual WC and taken to private exam room  placed on exam table in Trendelenberg position Ice packs provided to neck and axilla Placed under fan to help cool pt off. Pt stated still able to speak in full sentences without WOB, she had not eaten  much this morning prior to vaccine, had a coffee and a sweet cake nothing substantial. Losartan 25mg  x1 taken this morning for her HTN. At 1312 BP 138/102 auto cuff p68 Since pt felt her throat was getting tight, hands and mouth felt tingly and numb, "like she gets at home frequently." Vocal cord d/f listed as one of her medical issues. Provider asked pt if we can give her a benadryl shot, and she agreed. She was given benadryl 50mg IM  ( LOT# 019312, exp 1/21) in her left arm deltoid opposite of her Moderna shot arm.  Manual BP 138/102 p66 pursed lip mouth breathing. Guided pt to breath in through her nose slowly and slowly exhale through her mouth. 1317 Pt stated she was nauseated, provided zofran 4mg SL same as she takes at home. Pt started to feel better within 5m of the zofran. Afterward stated she felt better. At 1338 BP 130/96 p62 Oxygen 98% RA no WOB She was provided a small coca-cola and drank most of the can afterward began to feel better. Able to sit up. Speaking full sentences has baseline raspy voice per daughter due to the vocal cord d/f she has as her chronic medical issue. No WOB. Per daughter pt has these same "spells" often at home.   She was able to sit up, color came back to pts face, able to finish her soda and pt asked to eat something, provided a donut and able eat a donut while chatting. Pt stated she was feeling better. Since the temperature in the room was warm at the time,  the AC was turned down to make room cooler A cool pak was applied during the episode to the back of pts neck Pt felt her sxs resolved.   1345 Repeat BP 132/96 O2 sats 98% on RA   She verbalized she was feeling better and was grateful  for our care. Reminded pt to eat and drink prior to her next vaccine in 4 wks and we can prepare to observe her in an exam room  independently with a provider  or RN and have the benadryl and zofran on hand. Pt was able to walk with her daughter  to her car  in stable condition. Safety report filed.  A task sent to pts provider to help plan for pts second Moderna covid vaccine in 4 wks

I developed Idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura (low levels of platelets) and menorrhagia due to the vaccine according to my doctor. I believe there have been about 30 cases of this occurring so far.   In my case, I took the vaccine and felt relatively tired for two days. There were no other symptoms. About a week later, I got my period after not having it for a couple months. The blooding was light for a few days, but then got extremely heavy. After about a week of very heavy bleeding, I went to urgent care. They took blood tests, and found that I had a critically low level of platelets (6 platelets when the normal range is 150-400). I was admitted to the ER for multiple days, and they gave a platelet transfusion and IVIG  fluids, which has helped considerably. I also had to take steroids to suppress my immune system so that my platelets could increase.
LAB_DATA: Too many to name. Here are just a few of the tests that they took while I was in the hospital to try to determine the cause of the ITP.  Erythrocyte Sedimentation Rate - April 4th Automated reticulocyte Count - April 4th Lactate dehydrogenase - April 4th  White Blood Cell Differential - April 4th Anti Human Globulin (Coombs Test) - April 4th  ABO and RH Blood Typing - April 4th   I currently take biweekly blood tests to monitor my platelets.

One day after vaccination, a small, painful nodule developed on the left side of my nose just below the tear duct. About 12 hours later, it had grown to a large lump about 3.5 cm long and 1 cm wide, extending down and to the left of  my face. This was very painful. It led to significant swelling in the periorbital area. The swelling and pain continued through the next day. On the third day, I went to urgent care where I was diagnosed with cellulitis and put on 2 antibiotics (Augmentin and Clindamycin). The swelling and pain continued to get worse. On the 4th day, I went to ophthamology where I was referred to the emergency department. On the morning of the 5th day, I was finally seen in the ER. A CT scan and bloodwork were done. The CT scan showed no signs of an abscess and bloodwork was all normal. I was given doxycycline and stopped the clindamycin due to GI effects. I continued the Augmentin. On the 6th day, the swelling and pain were slightly less. I saw my PCP who referred me to infectious disease. I had a telehealth appointment on the 7th day with the ID specialist who encouraged me to submit a VAERS reports. Diagnosis is still listed as cellulitis. Today is the 8th day. The swelling and pain are significantly less pronounced, but the lump is still the same size and shape.
LAB_DATA: RBC sed rate, C-reactive protein, CBC with differential, metabolic panel (bloodwork normal), CT maxillofacial with contrast, (Findings most consistent with cellulitis of the left face, including the left infraorbital and left cheek/nose regions. No definite abscess formation. No subcutaneous soft tissue gas. No erosion of the underlying osseous structures. No evidence of left retro-orbital extension. Prominent nonenlarged left submandibular lymph node, likely reactive.)

At 12 pm he was having trouble breathing after just having been filled with 1500 ml of dialysate. This was the first time this happened. As I know that people who have serious diseases and are older are encouraged to take the vaccine, this outcome should be known to the CDC.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient had reported to the site for her second shot of COVID. During her assessment she did not mention any adverse reactions with the first shot. She did mention a hx of pseudoseizures during blood draws. She mentioned that her husband was waiting in the paring lot for her in case she had any reactions after her second shot, and that she would know during the first 15 minutes if she would have one or not. After receiving her vaccination, the patient reported to the observation area. The nurse in the observation area had checked on her, and in response the patient mentioned that her arm felt tingly. The nurse asked if this happened during her first shot, and she said yes. The patient then stated that she felt shaky. The nurse signaled for the medics to assess her further. The medics transferred as a two assist, as the patient was unable to support her own weight. The patient was then brought to a private area, and her husband was called by one of the nurses to come into the site per the patients request because he knew what to do for her when she had pseudoseizures. Medics maintained the patients safety throughout the event.  As the husband approached the entrance of the vaccine site, he was escorted to the private area where his wife was. Upon reaching his wife, the patient began to shake and breathing hard. The husband stated that she hadn't had any of these pseudoseizures in awhile and that it must have been from the shot. The medics advised bringing her to the hospital at that time for further evaluation and support, and the husband agreed.
HISTORY: Hx of pseudoseizures during blood draws
PRIOR_VAX: tingling in arm with the first vaccine, reported after second shot

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient reported that after getting the vaccine and sitting in the post-vaccination area for 15 minutes as instructed, starting feeling dizzy and a headache at the back of her head almost immediately after. I asked if she was feeling any other symptoms, she denied any and reported no trouble breathing or chest tightness. I took her blood pressure which came to be 143/98 and she stated that was high for her as she is always 120/80. I asked her questions regarding her PMH and she said she has hypothyroidism, IBS, and may have rheumatoid arthritis but it waiting on her tests with her physician. I kept her talking to assess for any changes but she was not improving, so I called EMS. Patient also stated she had a large meal before coming and she mentioned having a dish that had gluten in it even though she had a gluten allergy. When EMS arrived, they did a check-up and when escorting her to the ambulance truck patient was not able to take more than a few steps and needed to sit so they took her in a stretcher.
HISTORY: Hypothyroidism, IBS, and patient states that they may also have rheumatoid arthritis.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 3/2 - Received the first round of Moderna vaccination. No immediate side-effects noted.  I talked with my physician prior to getting the vaccine due to medical conditions and medications that I am taking. I was taking Xarelto due to chronic DVT/Blood clots in my left leg.   After 2.5 weeks I noted my left leg was swelling and I started to have discomfort in my leg. No noticeable changes to my leg at this time that made me concerned about getting the second vaccine.   3/30 - I received my second vaccination in the morning. I ended up going into the hospital at 4 pm due to numbness and pain in my left leg. I ended up being admitted to the hospital due to a DVT behind my L knee and in my femoral/iliac veins. I was also diagnosed with May-Thurbers syndrome. All the physicians, hematologists, and surgeons were surprised that I ended up with a severe blood clot as I was on Xarelto for over two years without an incident or problem. I did not have a fall or any change in my life that would have caused this issue to happen and they were all stumped.  I was switched to a heparin drip while Xarelto was clearing out of my system and in two days I had two stints put in my femoral/iliac vein on my left leg.  I was changed over to Lovenox and Coumadin 5-7.5 mg before leaving the hospital. There were no concerns and I was in the hospital from 3/30 to 4/3/21.  After I was discharged from the hospital I went to my primary care follow up on Tuesday 4/6/21. I was having increased pain behind my knee and overall not feeling well. I ended up having more labs completed and another ultrasound to indicate I had a small DVT behind my knee from my procedure.   On Friday 4/9/21 I went in for my INR and found my coumadin was within therapeutic range. When I got home I changed into comfy clothing and noted that I had a red/purplish rash looking dots/bumps from my toes to my knees on both LE, my Left was more significant than my right. I went back into the doctor and I was prescribed a topical steroid to help decrease the edema, pain and redness.   Saturday 4/10/21 - my legs became painful to the touch, they felt like they were going to burst due to pressure, and the rash/reddness was looking worse and spreading. I was sent back to the ER and was admitted back to the hospital. They diagnosed me with heparin-induced thrombocytopenia, removed me off of coumadin, and started me on Arixtra. The hematologist, physicians and staff did not know what to do and I was now deemed medically complex and had to be monitored for a few days and gave me prednisone. Once removed from coumadin the rash/pain/swelling subsided and started to diminish. I was discharged from the hospital.  I returned to work on Tuesday 4/13 and after returning home I had increased pain, pressure and rash that now was visible from my knees to my hips and this was not present in the hospital. My physician is asking for a biopsy and increased my prednisone to stay at 20 mg a day.  At night I have to elevate my legs or they become swollen and will become painful.   4/16/21 I wore compression tights per physician guidelines and when I came home from work I had new spots and rashes on my feet, they were swollen and had increased pain. My left ankle had a rash on it as well. After elevation and a nights rest the rash started to diminish and the rest of my legs have started to diminish or disappear.

patient is 63-year-old male, active smoker with no history of hypercoagulability or malignancy is admitted in hospital for DVT in left popliteal vein.  He received first dose of Pfizer vaccine for COVID about 1 week ago. Patient's PTT was high on presentation even before being started on heparin.  Due to sudden drop in hemoglobin patient's heparin drip was suspended since 4/12.  Mixing studies showed partial correction consistent with acquired factor inhibitor.  Factor VIII levels less than 1 consistent with factor VIII inhibitor. Patient was started on FEIBA at 100 units/kg every 12 hours, tolerated very well,  In order to eliminate the inhibitor immunosuppressive therapy was initiated: Will continue Solu-Medrol 80 mg daily and Cytoxan 2 mg/kg daily.  This treatment will continue until his clinical stability is achieved, at which point taper will be initiated.  Patient required 2 transfusion over the course of the hospitalization. Currently, he is stable but still hospitalized and receiving treatments. No signs of new bleeds.

CUR_ILL: Symptoms resembling "long COVID" or PASC for 13 months. Had a severe possibly life-threatening respiratory illness in March 2020, was unable to get a test to confirm infection. Had oxygen levels dip to below 85% via home pulse oximeter and severe shortness of breath, chest tightness, fever, and inability to work, lasting up 6 weeks. Slow recovery over the rest of the year, with occasional flare-ups including neurological symptoms such as pains in the head, seizure-like sensations, heart palpitations, chest pains, and pressurized feeling in ear blocking hearing (similar to during a flight). Flare-ups occurred with a random set of symptoms each time, but were milder through 2021 compared to how debilitating they were before. Was feeling almost back to normal.
HISTORY: See item 11. Long COVID-19, aka Post-Acute Sequelae of COVID-19 (PASC) is the most likely diagnosis given the symptoms I have had ongoing for 13+ months since March 2020.

During 15 min waiting period patient developed lightheadedness and dizziness with heart racing.  No chest pain or chest tightness.  She felt weak and unable to walk.  At first was thought to be a vasovagal reaction and she was given po fluids and monitored.  Vitals were stable.  HR was in the 70s with a baseline of 50s.  She began to feel somewhat better in terms of the lightheadedness and dizziness and was able to walk to "clinic" area at the vaccination event.  Her heart rate was fluctuating between 50 and 107 and otherwise vitals remained normal.  Blood pressure up a bit more than likely due to anxiety.  BP 132/90;  HR 50 - 107;  Rep 20; P.O. 98%; denied pain.  She was given 25mg diphenhydramine IM.  No complaint of throat closing, no anaphylaxis.  She continued to feels waves of tachycardia.  Rescue squad dispatched for further management and observation to make sure no delayed anaphylactic reaction.  Her course at the ED was benign.  No further management other than fluids.  Urine pregnancy test was negative.  No bloodwork completed.  Patient observed four hours with no adverse event and left ED feeling her normal self.  At no time had anaphylactic reaction.
ALLERGIES: NKDA.  No food or other allergies

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was on day 2 of my period on the day I got vaccine dose #1. I had no symptoms immediately following vaccination at around 3PM other than a very sore arm at the injection site. At around 12AM, I woke up experiencing chills and headache. I fell back asleep but woke up later at around 2AM. I got out of bed to urinate and as I was finishing, I experienced extreme and sudden lightheadedness which led to a loss of conciousness and I subsequently fell off the toilet and onto my bathroom floor. I came to and began experiencing the worst abdominal cramps that I have ever had in my life, as well as headache, nausea, and chills. My husband helped me to sit up, but I felt that I was about to pass out again and laid back down. I drank a glass of water and took an Advil, and after about 30 minutes of experiencing severe symptoms, I felt strong enough to sit up, and eventually to walk back to bed. I wear a that measures heart rate and my heart rate during this time dropped to as low as 44bpm (resting is normally around 55bpm). Since the episode I have felt much better, although still a bit "off". I have yet to visit my doctor but plan to seek advice prior to getting the second dose.
ALLERGIES: Allergy to Ceclor Intolerance to avocados

SYMPTOM_TEXT: In summary this is a 60 year old male who was normal functioning presenting to hospital 4 days following second moderna COVID-19 vaccination with AKI, Rhabdomyolsis, Confusion/Delirium with agitation, multiple acute brain infarcts, DVT, and multilobar pulmonary embolism.  24 hours following vaccination patient began to become slightly confused while driving his wife to her vaccine appointment.  Symptoms progressed and included severe fatigue and muscle aches.  Patient was taking tizanidine and oxycodone to manage muscle / body aches which had been prescribed for his chronic back pain issues.  Patient was noted to be excessively sleeping, and also had fallen twice between vaccination and hospital presentation. 4 days following vaccination he presented to the emergency department with severe lethargy and confusion.  He was admitted with presumption of overdose of medication, given activated charcoal.  A CT of the head (4/11/2021) was completed which demonstrated No acute intracranial hemorrhage, extra-axial fluid collection or acute territorial infarct. Suggestion of a chronic lacunar infarct involving the left lentiform nucleus. Regions of low attenuation involving the cerebellar hemispheres, right greater than left, which, allowing for image degradation secondary to patient motion artifact, are likely artifactual in nature; follow-up is recommended to assess for stability/resolution.For first several days patient suffered delirium with agitation, he was disoriented to place and time.  CK on admission, 4/11/2021, was 17,086, indicating rhabdo.  Creatinine on admission was 4.39, indicating new acute renal failure. Liver enzymes were elevated with AST of 477 and ALT of 218. PT was 10.6, INR 0.99.  ABG demonstrated metabolic acidosis with pH of 7.22, co2 45, HCO3 18.4.  Over several days his mentation improved however was noted to still need light supplemental oxygenation.  Because of the delirium a brain MRI was completed on 4/13/2021, which demonstrated acute ischemic infarcts on DWI sequence noting bilateral, right greater than left, acute cerebellar infarcts. Small acute lacunar infarcts at bilateral basal ganglia/genu internal capsule.  Due to the infarcts a stroke workup was completed. Carotid duplex was performed and notable for only small bilateral carotid plaque.  Renal ultrasound unremarkable.  A CTA of the chest was completed on 4/15/2021 for continued hypoxemia, need for nasal cannula to maintain spo2 saturation.  Findings included multilobar pulmonary embolism.  Venous duplex dopplers of the lower extremities were also completed on 4/15/2021 demonstrated an isolated left popliteal vein DVT. No evidence of right leg DVT.  Over several days CK and Cr returned to baseline / normal levels.  He remains hospitalized and is still undergoing treatment.
OTHER_MEDS: mirtazapine (REMERON) 30 mg tablet   amLODIPine (NORVASC) 10 mg tablet  atorvastatin (LIPITOR) 20 mg tablet  celecoxib (CeleBREX) 200 mg capsule  clidinium-chlordiazepoxide (Librax, with clidinium,) 5-2.5 mg per capsule  oxyCODONE-acetamino
HISTORY: Chronic Low Back Pain Hypertension Hypercholesterolemia BPH Arthritis Insomnia neuropathy

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 9:30am About 10 minutes post vaccine client came to desk stating, "my hand feels funny and I feel a little funny". Taken into quiet area, color pink, skin warm and dry.  Denies dyspnea or pain. Offers no concerns after first vaccine. States left hand felt tingly so took watch off thinking it was too tight and states, "then I felt a rush like I might faint but that passed."  BP on right - 226/120, pulse regular and strong at 88.  Denies numbness or tingling anywhere else other than left hand.  Speech clear. No drooping noted of face.  Offers has been on BP pills for about 20 years - no change in prescription, no recent BP check, "due for annual". Took BP pill at 7:30am. BP 180/100, pulse remains regular at 86 and strong. No changes noted in color. Offers feeling improved with mask down. Offers breakfast of cake and coffee. BP rechecked and 200/120.  Discussed going to Urgent Care for recheck and called husband to come to transport. Offers some tingling continues in left hand only - otherwise feels good.  BP 230/98 on right and 160/98 on right. States "I'm feeling better" but still states that left hand remains slightly numb.  Husband arrived. 9:55 Right BP 188/80 left 170/100.  Pulse remains strong and regular at 88.  Left with husband to seek care at urgent care. Given list of BP readings and requested husband to let us know outcome. This note has been signed and cannot be modified. SYMPTOM_TEXT: At approximately 1035, approximately 15 minutes after receiving first Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine, patient was walking out to leave and this RN overheard her state nausea and feeling hot.  This RN intercepted patient in the hallway and advised that she come sit down.  Patient diaphoretic and not completely coherent.  She responded appropriately to questions and instruction, but was slow to respond and gait slow.  Patient denied feeling dizziness and like she would fall at the time.  Patient escorted to recliner, feet elevated, head reclined.  Patient evaluated by this RN and NP.  Vitals at 1040  96.1 degrees F (temporal artery) 110/60, manual right Heart rate 84 bpm, regular 99%, room air Respirations 20/minute  LS clear and equal throughout. No respiratory distress.  Patient denied throat tightness/swelling.  No rash or itching present.  Patient denies history of reactions to vaccines or medications.  Allergies in electronic medical record reviewed with patient as accurate (dust, hay, nickel).  Patient denies history of diabetes or issues with blood sugar or medications that effect blood sugar.  Patient reported that she ate blueberries and _____ today.    She was provided graham crackers, water, and apple juice.  Patient improved quickly.  Diaphoresis and feeling hot resolved.  Nausea resolved.  At this time, patient reported that she had felt nausea within a few minutes after receiving the vaccine.  That escalated to diaphoresis and feeling warm with dizziness approximately 10-15 minutes later.    At 1100, symptoms resolved.  Vitals: 98.1 degrees F (temporal artery) 116/88, manual right Heart rate 88 bpm, regular 100%, room air Respirations 24/minute  LS clear and equal throughout. No respiratory distress.  Patient denied throat tightness/swelling.  No rash or itching present.  Patient stated that she feels much better and feels safe to leave.  Symptoms of delayed allergic reaction and when to seek medical care discussed.   Encouraged patient to eat and hydrate well prior to second COVID vaccine and to inform vaccinator of today's event.  Recommended that she stay for monitoring longer (at least 30 minutes).    Patient verbalized understanding.  All questions answered at this time.  Patient evaluated and examined by this RN and NP who agrees patient safe to discharge home at this time.  At 1105, patient discharged home.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Despite having a dedicated vaccination station for teenagers where only Pfizer Vaccine is provided, this patient apparently indicated to our vaccinator that he was there for Moderna (as his entire family had already received that).   The patient appeared several years older than his actual age of 16 and the vaccinator said that he stated he was over 18.  However, the vaccinator neglected to check his date of birth in the system to confirm it.  The patient's mother was in the room but was not present at the vaccination station where he was seated.  Believing the patient was an adult, the vaccinator walked two tables away to retrieve a dose of Moderna and vaccinated the patient with it.  Within minutes our team recognized that we had one dose too many of Pfizer and one too few of Moderna and we realized what had happened.   The patient had absolutely no adverse reaction whatsoever but this error was quite disconcerting to my entire team.  This incident was fully discussed afterwards with the patient's mother who, interestingly, appeared pleased that he had received the Moderna vaccine as his whole family already had as well.  Clearly the family doesn't recognize the mandates and safety measures implemented by the CDC and vaccine manufacturers but that is a separate issue.  We have a strict policy in place that patients don't request one vaccine over another.  They are administered in a thoughtful, meticulous fashion based on CDC and manufacturer guidelines.  We don't take requests and we don't breach those guidelines.   Additional training was provided to this vaccinator and to my entire staff to ensure this never happens again.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I woke-up on 4/7 with an itchy throat and hives were starting to form on my stomach.  As the day went on, the hives were all over my torso and went up to my neck as well.  When I have hives on my neck, they usually start to bother my asthma/breathing, and this happened on 4/7 as well.  My allergist said to up the dosage of Allegra 24 hours from 2 tablets a day to 4.  I also took my Albuterol inhaler to control the wheezing.  My doctor also gave me a prescription for Prednisone in case I needed it over the weekend, and recommended I go to the ER if my symptoms got worse.  Luckily, the extra Allegra and asthma inhaler calmed by symptoms down.   Things calmed down over the weekend and by 4/14, the hives were completely gone and I was not longer experiencing any side effects.  I did not need to do any in-person doctor's visits; I just talked to my doctor on the phone.  Please note that I also had the 'flu-like' symptoms after the shot as well.  I felt great after the shot and even exercised on my elliptical around 7:45 that night.  At around 9:00, I had extreme chills, where my body was shaking, as well as sweating.  I also had extreme fatigue, a headache, and some body aches as well.  I slept for 16 hours that night and felt somewhat better when I got up.  By that late that night, all the flu-like symptoms were gone.   I took some Tylenol for the headache.
OTHER_MEDS: Pravulent 150 mg, Advair, multi-vitamin, vitamin D3, COQ10, fish oil, Tylenol, Allegra (Per my allergist, two 24-hour tablets a day for three days before and after vaccine.  She had me take four a day to calm down my reaction on 4/9/21.)

No nausea.   Patient continued to complain of dizzyness while itchy sensation diminishing.  Vital signs BP 118/70  Hr 78, RR 16. .  Color remains pink.  No rash.  Itching only in upper extremeties.  Legs elevated on chair.  Pt refused to lay on stretcher.  Stated she no longer felt dizzy and only left arm itched. Eating protein bar.  Vital signs rechecked after standing patient upright.   BP 116/78 HR 80 RR 20.  Pt wanting to go home.  Observed her for 30 minutes post benadryl injection.  Ambulated out of observation area symptom free and insisted on driving self home.  Warning signs reviewed regarding vaccine reaction and aware to react to the onset of further or worsening adverse vaccine reaction.

I was 9 months pregnant at the time of the vaccination. My due date was April 3, 2021. The actual date of delivery was March 20, 2021 by C-section. I gave birth to a son weighing 8 lbs 6 oz. I had no complications during this pregnancy. I left the hospital on March 22nd. On March 25, I was experiencing shortness of breath and a low pulse (35 bpm; my usual pulse is in the 50s-60s). My OBGYN told me to go to the emergency room, where they did a CT scan. The CT scan showed a small pulmonary embolism. I was in the hospital until March 27th, where I was treated with Heparin and then was released with Lovenox injections. I am currently on the Lovenox. After seeing the pulmonologist for a follow-up appointment, he advised me that I would be able to stop the injections after 3 months.
LAB_DATA: CT Scan 3/26 - pulmonary embolism, EKG 3/26 - normal, Echocardiogram 3/26 - normal, ultrasound of legs 3/27 - normal, blood tests - normal

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was 22 weeks along with my third pregnancy (second viable) and my due date is 8/8/21. I received the Pfizer vaccine on Thursday, April 8, 2021. On Friday, April 9, around 1pm, I began to feel a lot of fatigue, slight body aches and started to come down with a slight fever of 99 degrees F. I called my OBGYN doctor's office to see if they would recommend I begin taking the Tylenol I already had on hand just in case I started to have a fever and they said to go ahead and take it (2 capsules every 6 hours as needed). After taking the first two capsules at 2pm and the first six hours had passed, I took another 2 capsules and checked my temperature again. This time it was at 100.6 (my doctor said a fever starts at 100.1). I continued to monitor my temperature every couple of hours and it went back down quickly and never came up again while I was taking the Tylenol (I took the capsules around 2pm, 8pm. The body aches also subsided, but the fatigue continued. I took my last 2 Tylenol capsules around 3am on Saturday, April 10, 2021.  On Saturday, I only felt slightly fatigued and much better than Friday and by Sunday, I was fine.
Possible vasovagal near syncope post vaccination.  Transferred to ED for evaluation.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within minutes after receiving 2nd dose of Pfizer COVID vaccine (at approximately 1200) patient presented to this RN due to complaints of feeling like she would pass out. Mask taken off due to complaints of "having a hard time breathing." Patient complained of LEFT sided chest pain; unable to determine if this pain is acute or chronic. Patient slow to respond and unable to describe symptoms well. Patient slow to respond to questioning. Patient with mildly stuttered speech. Eventually patient admitted to dizziness.   Given the nature of presentation, First responder called and arrived quickly.   Vitals at 1200:   135/112, semi-Fowler's position, right arm 84 bpm, apical, regular 95%, room air  Patient denied swelling, throat tightness. No rash.   Patient sat up in chair to help with breathing.   Vitals at 1212:  Heart rate 101 bpm. No apparent respiratory distress. NP briefly auscultated prior to immediate transport to Emergency Department. Per NP, patient with =1/6 systolic murmur and tachycardic, on auscultation. Per NP Patient's LS clear and equal bilaterally, bases mildly diminished.    Patient transported to Emergency Department via wheelchair with First Responder.

Some of this muscle fluttering and twitching preceded muscle cramping in the feet. Frequency was almost continuous with short, 60 second pauses between twitches. The moved and we?re not in the same exact location. We?re especially active when when lying flat, relaxed in bed. All symptoms aside from the twitching subsided fully by the following Morning (April 15th 2021). Took body temp that morning and had returned to 98.7 f.  Muscle twitches have continued  five days beyond vaccination, although they have grown milder and less frequent.

I got the vaccine on 4/7/21 at approx. 10am. Soreness at injection site started about an hour later. At approx. 3pm that day I began to have body aches and chills and had a low grade fever and a very bad and continuous headache. Those symptoms lasted approx. 24-36 hours. By Friday 4/9, I was feeling better and fever was gone. Starting approx. Sun 4/11 I began to have a dull headache wrapping around the back of my head/neck and began having muffled hearing (bilateral, but more prominent in left ear). On 4/15 at approx. 1:15pm I was sitting at my desk and suddenly my heart rate went from resting heart rate to 150. I could feel the pounding in my head and ear and also placing my hand over my heart. I tried to stand up to walk around thinking that might help my heart rate, but I felt faint, so I immediately drove myself to urgent care. My heart rate came down and was back to normal approx. 5-10 min from onset. EKG and CT were done in the ER. I was released approx. 5-6 hours after arrival and told to treat headache with Tylenol or Ibuprofen (which I have not done so far because I normally try not to take medications), and follow up with my primary doctor in a week. Headache and muffled hearing are still present today (4/17), predominately affecting left ear.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: At 1450 patient approached Paramedic with concern regarding left wrist pain and vein protruding more than right. Paramedic  noted that client was able to ambulate to chair in observation without assistance and with a steady gait. Client rated the pain as 2/10 on a 0-10 pain scale and was non-radiating. Paramedic observed there was no asymmetry between left and right wrists, there was mild distention of left radial vein, negative for pain on palpation, negative for temperature difference between right and left extremity. At 1502 client began to complain of neck discomfort, then a headache on forehead which she rated a 5/10. Client reported a history of epilepsy and stated she has a headache aura prior to seizures. Paramedic advised client to sit in the zero gravity chair for further assessment and noted client was able to ambulate to chair on her own accord and with a steady gait. Client denied complaints of dizziness, shortness of breath, blurry vision.  At 1508  client stated left radial pain was gone, headache was now rated a 3/10. Client was given a bottle of water. At 1510 vitals were taken with client sitting in zero gravity chair: blood pressure 110/80, respiratory rate: 14, heartrate: 78, client was alert and oriented to time, space, situation and person (CAOx4). Client stated symptoms were diminishing. At 1520 a second set of vitals were taken: Blood pressure: 112/82, Respiratory rate: 14, Heartrate: 78, CAOx4. Client stated she had no complaints. Client was advised to stay an additional 15 minutes. At 1540 client released from observation and she left the observation site on her own accord with a steady gait.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Immediate muscle tension in left arm  following vaccine shot in left arm.  The soreness persisted for several days. Painful to lift left arm higher than my shoulder.  The morning of day 3, I woke up to feel a pronounced skin irritation under my left armpit.  Later that day, I noticed a small welt on my left arm and the irritation had grown to include my upper left arm front and back. Over the next few days, the number of welts increased and the pain was increasing from the skin irritation. The tension in my shoulder started to give way to feeling tightness in my left chest.   I reported the symptoms. I tried to report to the Health Department, but they wouldn't take a report stating that the symptoms I was reporting did not match "known symptoms".  On 4/13/21, I went to the Urgent Care to have the rash examined. The doctor tentatively diagnosed as Shingles. However, because of the chest pain, he referred to the Emergency Room for blood tests to rule out a possible Pulmonary Embolism.  The blood tests came back normal. I was prescribed 12 Hydrocodone-Acetaminophen for the pain and discharged.  On 4/15/21 I returned to Urgent Care because the welts were continuing to spread and the pain was increasing. Including sharp pains associated with the shingles. At this visit I was prescribed 21 tablets of Hydrocodone-Acetaminophen and 21 tablets of ValACYclovir.
LAB_DATA: See above or contact medical providers for more information.

Patient presents following administration of the second dose of Moderna COVID19 vaccine in the left deltoid.  Patient stated that 20 minutes following administration of the vaccine, the patient started to experience an itching sensation in her left shoulder, neck, and right shoulder.  She denies decrease in muscle strength or difficulty swallowing.  She relates that a similar experience also happened following administration of the first dose of Moderna vaccine.  She related that it lasted for about 2 hours and went away without intervention.  She did not seek medical attention.  She denies allergies to medication, vaccines, and food.  She denies a past medical history.  She does not take medication on a regular basis.  She denies chest pain, difficulty breathing, swelling of the face/lips/tongue/throat, skin rash/itching, cramping abdominal pain, nausea, and vomiting.     Exam (update as needed): GEN: Alert and oriented x 4, NAD. HEAD: NCAT EYES: PERRL, EOMI ENT: Ears normal, Nose normal, OP normal, no evidence of angioedema NECK: Supple, without LAD.  CV: RRR, no m/r/g PULM: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no accessory muscle use ABD: Soft, no tenderness. SKIN: No rashes, skin warm and dry.  No erythema or edema of the injection site. MSK: FROM, MS 5/5 NEURO: Alert and oriented x 4, CN 2-12 grossly intact, no ataxia, gait steady   Clinical Impression/Field Tx: Paresthesias related to vaccination.  No acute skin manifestations or anaphylactic manifestations that require emergent intervention.  Vitals signs stable.  Symptoms are stable.  Patient was driven to the site by significant other and stated they would take PO Benadryl once they arrive at home. They do not intend to operate heavy machinery for the remainder of the day.  Further instructed patient about what vaccine side effects to expect following second dose administration and appropriate interventions/at home care.   Instructed patient to consult their PCP regarding the post-vaccination reaction.  Patient instructed to go to emergency department should they develop chest pain, difficulty breathing, swelling of the face/lips/mouth/tongue/throat, or cramping abdominal pain with nausea/vomiting, as these are signs of possible anaphylaxis that requires immediate intervention.     Medications administered: None   Disposition:  Home
PRIOR_VAX: Similar paresthesias with administration of first dose of Moderna vaccine 4 weeks prior

I felt as if the symptoms were similar to pericarditis and after my trip to the ED I experienced transient chest pain during the day along with at night.  I took ibuprofen 800mg TID, which helped to alleviate the chest pain for most of the evening and day.  The chest pain ceased on 2/26/21 and I have not experienced it since. SYMPTOM_TEXT: My 20-year-old son received his first Moderna shot on March 16, 2021, at his college health clinic with no obvious side effects. He received the second Moderna shot at the same location on April 13, 2021. On the morning of April 14, 2021, he began running a high fever with repetitive vomiting and stomach cramping. He did not immediately seek medical attention because he had been told of side effects of the vaccine. When it was no longer tolerable, he reported to the local ER where it was later discovered he had a 4 mm kidney stone, which he passed two days later. We were told that the kidney stone would likely have begun forming about 31 days earlier, which would approximately coincide with his first COVID injection. There is no family history on either side of any kidney stones in the family. While my son's lifestyle may introduce some risk factors for kidney stones, I felt it was reasonable to report it as potentially relating to the vaccine.
LAB_DATA: CBC lab work was done, as well as a CT scan, which identified the 4 mm kidney stone.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On about April 8th, 2021 I began to experience a sharp stabbing pain in my lower left shoulder blade that would throb persistently. My upper back and my left underarm area on my torso towards my back began to hurt and become extremely sensitive to touch. My lymph nodes in my left armpit, left collarbone, and on the left side of my neck were and still are very swollen. I initially went to the doctor on April 14th, 2021 after dealing with this pain that was getting progressively worse. I feared that I was having a pulmonary embolism or a cardiac event, and maybe even a problem with my spleen. After examination, my doctor believed the culprit to be my inflamed lymph nodes causing inflammation in the surrounding areas. My doctor sent me home with Meloxicam and Flexeril to help with my pain. On the night of April 14th, 2021 I noticed a rash under my left breast beginning to form. Over the course of the next 3 days, the rash became a cluster of blisters, I developed severe shooting pains from my left breast into my under arm area and around my back along the left side. My spine in my upper back began to feel bruised, along with my sternum which feels bruised and inflamed internally. I've been so uncomfortable that I've been having trouble sleeping. The pain also worsens after I eat, which makes eating really difficult. I made a second doctor's appointment for today, April 17th, 2021 (I was unable to get a sooner appointment) . My doctor confirmed that the rash is in fact Shingles and she prescribed me Valtrex and Percocet for the pain. I am currently taking these medications. Because I just found out my diagnosis today, I am still in severe pain and it's been 14 days since my second Pfizer vaccine. I do not have any known autoimmune disorders.
ALLERGIES: Penicillin Augmentin Zithromax Nickel Adhesive tape

About an hour later, I started noticing it hurt my arm socket to move my arm certain ways. Over the remainder of the night, it became increasingly worse, causing a sharp pain in the socket when I would move my arm at all, to the point where it was excruciating to try to undress for bed. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my 1st dose of Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine on 4/14/21 at 11:30am with the  Fire Department.. I left at 12:00 after being cleared and noticed 30 minutes later a red ring forming around the injection site.  I contacted me PCP where she told me to take Tylenol and Benadryl and if symptoms got worse, to proceed to an urgent care clinic.  Wednesday afternoon until Saturday morning, the injection site become extremely painful, hot to the touch and I was having a difficult time moving my elbow and fingers.  I proceeded to the urgent care clinic around 4pm on Saturday 4/17/21 after being diligent about taking OTC medications directed by my doctor as well as ice packs on the injection site.  At the urgent care clinic I was told I was having a non-systemic allergic reaction at the injection site where I was given a steroid shot and also given a prescription for a 5 day course of prednisone.  The area was very hot to the touch, hard and spreading.  Doctor was concerned and  said to contact CDC and that he would be hesitant to take the 2nd shot in the vaccine series after seeing this reaction.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient fainted shortly after receiving second dose of Moderna Covid vaccine. When I approached the patient he was laying on the ground and very pale but still breathing. I rolled him onto his back and elevated his feet and asked him to keep breathing and try to stay calm. I asked someone to grab him some water and someone else to run to the pharmacy and grab the pharmacy manager while I monitored the patient. I asked if I could help him sit up to drink some water and he accepted. After sitting up I asked if he had eaten and if I could get him something to eat. He stated he hadn't eaten all day and that he had a panic disorder and felt like he was having a panic attack. I asked if he had medicine he needed to take to help him feel better, he stated no, he needed to just wait it out. Then he told me he felt like he was going to throw up and I got him a waste basket that he threw up in right away. I asked the patient if he hit his head or if he wanted us to call an ambulance; he stated no to both questions. The pharmacy manager arrived and sat with the patient for the next half hour or more until he felt better. He stated that his dad was going to take him home now that he felt better. Some store staff had us fill out an incident report and the pharmacy manager walked the customer out to his car where he said he would call and find his dad.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: A 46 y.o. male who presents today with numbness in both legs, difficulty concentrating and forgetfulness, and cough with chest tightness. Covid symptomatic in November.   Received Covid Pfizer vaccine on 4.13.21 at 1pm. Felt fine headed into the vaccine. He completed the observation period and felt chest tightness after about 5 minutes similar to Covid in November. He felt slightly better and went to work. At work his cough and chest tightness worsened. Very tired, unable to eat with no appetite. Extreme fatigue Wednesday sleeping most of the day. Cough and chest tightness and feeling he cannot catch breath like being submerged in a pool. On 4.15.21 his feet became numb and tingling bilaterally. He felt more confusion, forgetting what he was doing, left frozen food in the sink and unable to recall why. He is also having headache posteriorly 7-8/10 which began on 4.14.21. He reports headache is not common, now 3-4/10 and feels very similar to Covid in November. Does have some mild neck stiffness associated. Chest tightness almost identical to Covid in November.  Reports numbness and tingling in the feet has been ascending in nature. He felt unsteady on his feet yesterday morning. He is having tingling and cramping in the bilateral calf muscles today. His cough continues with no phlegm. Comes in coughing spells with chest tightness. He also noted cough is worse with exertion. Fever 99.8 yesterday.  No diarrhea. No loss of smell or taste.   In ED noted to have right LE weakness.  Wife reports that he seemed unsteady while walking Kept for observation.   difficulty concentrating - back to baseline 4/17/21 at 3:26 pm assessment SOB: CTA thorax 4/16/21 unremarkable CT angiogram thorax Symptoms began approximately 5 minutes after his Pfizer.  Reports that his cough and shortness of breath now seems to be improving.  Continues to have some mild chest tightness, intermittent cough.  Robitussin significantly helped.  Extensive workup including CT angiogram of the thorax reveals no evidence for pulmonary embolism or infiltrate.  COVID-19 PCR testing is negative x2, severe respiratory isolation has been discontinued.  Patient has a negative D-dimer, LDH, ferritin, CRP.   Cardiac troponin has been negative x2.  Patient does have some wheeze, after cough, suggesting some bronchospasm.  Will trial albuterol inhaler q.i.d..  Patient does report a history of what sounds like an environmental triggers asthma like event in the past, though reports that he has undergone evaluation for asthma and was told that he does not carry a diagnosis of asthma.  Patient is currently on room air.  I have reviewed the reported adverse reactions from the Pfizer vaccine and coughing shortness of breath are not listed.  Continue supportive care, with Tessalon and Robitussin, IS
LAB_DATA: MRI imagining of the brain & cervical spine - unrevealing cardiac work up unremarkable EKG sinus arrhythmia with sinu bradycaria troponin x2 negative CT angiogram of the chest abdomen & pelvis negative for dissection COVID 19 PCR pending in am

My calf muscle swelled and became very painful; my lower leg was covered with black and blue bruises; my varicose veins reappeared. These problems diminished slowly throughout February. I saw a specialist at the Vein Clinic in March, who determined that I needed additional surgery this summer. My leg has almost returned to normal, but I have intermittent heaviness in the calf muscle and pain in the quads, like a weaker version of what I had before the first vein surgery in 2018.  Additional comments: I had a bout of powerful fatigue following the first shot. I slept 14 hours straight the day after getting it. For the second shot, the fatigue was less severe, coming in waves. However, I felt weak for more than two months, which I noticed since I go to the gum regularly. My strength has still not returned to where it was previously.

Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine: The PQCF was reviewed with the patient who stated that she was feeling ok today: no cough, diarrhea, vomiting and didn't require a tetanus shot for an injury. The patient did state that she was allergic to Penicillin and that she had just completed a course of antibiotics Cipro 500mg for an UTI. After she was administered the Moderna vaccine 1st dose, the patient was advised to sit for a couple of minutes near the pharmacy area where she had just taken her shot while her husband was administered his vaccine and then they would be walked up together to the Post-Vaccination Sitting Area. The patient sat near the pharmacy for roughly 5-10 minutes and then walked over to one of the pharmacy Counseling windows to let us know that she was feeling funny and weird. No sooner than she uttered those words, she collapsed and fainted. 911 was called. Once conscious the patient stated that she truly wasn't feeling the best before getting the vaccine but wanted to go ahead and get her vaccine today. EMTs checked vitals. Her blood pressure and blood sugar were normal; however, her heart rate was low and skin turgor was poor. Her preliminary diagnosis before being transported to a nearby hospital was dehydration. I truly do not think that the vaccine caused her syncope spell but reporting since event occurred shortly after Moderna was administered.
OTHER_MEDS: The patient stated that she had just completed a course of antibiotics, Cipro 500mg for UTI.
CUR_ILL: The patient stated that she had just completed a course of antibiotics for an UTI.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Standard sore arm started within a few hours; other muscle aches and headache started as the day went on. These were expected. Potentially more unusually, I woke up on 4/17 with a wheal on my face, which could just be my chronic hives acting up independently, but then in the evening of 4/17 I noticed a raised red mark on my arm near the injection site, which also looks like a wheal, as well as a wheal in the shape of the sticky portion of the bandaid used post-vaccination (which I?d removed before bed on 4/16). I?d had a similar wheal on my arm a few days after the first shot (given 3/19), so seeing another one now makes me believe it may be connected to the vaccine. The wheal is below the injection site (about 7 o?clock if you?re standing looking at the injection site) and seems to be raised like a bump and is both hot and tender to the touch . It is unlike my normal wheals in location (more commonly I get them on the underside of my forearm), size, and characteristics, and because it is NOT itchy like they usually are. The wheal on my face was darker than usual, more a wine than bright red, and not in a typical location (it was high on the cheekbone just under my right eye; I most often get one on the left cheekbone near my nose). However, it was itchy in the way my wheals usually are. It is faded but still present and no longer itchy as of this submission, which is normal for my facial wheals.
OTHER_MEDS: Nature Made Postnatal vitamin 1/day for breastfeeding support; Nature Made Calcium 600mg with 400 IU vitamin D 2/day for breastfeeding support; Nature Made Vitamin D 2000 IU 2/day; Zyrtec 10mg as needed for chronic hives
PRIOR_VAX: As mentioned in my description, I had a similar wheal on my arm after after my first dose of Moderna, but i didn?t see that one

I felt light headed when I tried to get out of bed.  For the next 24 hours, I ran a temperature, had an extreme headache, had an ear ache in my right ear and my right sinus hurt.  Again, I could not get out of bed.  After around 48 hours, the fever broke, but I still felt like I had an extreme migraine, my right sinus hurt and my right ear hurt.  Light hurt my eyes. I spent 72 hour sleeping.  I drank hot tea and ate a little soup during this time, but that was all.  I felt HORRID for three full days.  This was MUCH longer than I expected.  If you decide we need booster shots, I hope you figure out what was making me feel so horrible.  I can't imagine going through this for three days every time I get a booster.  Thank you for making the vaccine.  I do feel like it will protect me.

The patient lives with her elderly mother and has a brother whom she is responsible for. The patient was now concerned that she is still very much in a situation where she could get sick and that it could be severe. The patient would like to know why this vaccine did not generate antibodies and if there is a booster. It is concerning that she has no antibodies. The patient recovered from the events in Mar2021.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I started feeling random sharp "nerve stabs." I was walking and felt a bit odd just because I almost immediately tasted a metal taste in my mouth and commented on it and something seemed "off." As I kept walking it off, the pharmacist came to check up on me but I was still trying to figure out what was wrong. Over the next 15 minutes, I had a "heavy knee" feeling under both knee caps at the same time, tingling on the bottom of both feet at the same time like they were placed against a jet and both jaws tightened in one location...not at the TMJ but lower....like where my jaws misaligned from the accident. And then heavy eye brows would hit. And they wouldn't stay like this. It would come and go. Come and go. Not in seconds but 10 minute intervals or something? But I definitely was starting to feel more "nervy." Not prickly. Not pain. Just random sharp here and there or feeling like I could feel a nerve "wake up" here and there. Also, my hips/pelvis. On both sides at the same time they would not ache but get tight or say HI in a weird way but more towards the glute/pelvis region; it was an odd location. Also. My lower back was tight. It got really tight. That was the most annoying thing. It stayed tight. Also, my right shoulder/neck that had been locked up and inflammed from a flare-up...the pain disappeared just like my head pain. (The nerve issues sometimes felt like when I took rizaptriptan the first few times and I could feel the nerve then too.   Due to being used to weird nerve issues since the accident, I was concerned but not enough to go to the hospital and just wanted to wait it out. I had plans of going home and working out and doing my therapy and stretches.   I got home and within 45 minutes of the vaccine my face was starting to feel cold. I was feeling nervy all over. And then my spinal cord lit up, just once, like electrifying....not painful....but like electricity....like nerve. A large section of it just lit up and then that was it. I didn't have any odd movements with it. It just lit up.   Also, my head. There was a spot on the top of my head near the "soft spot" that I kept feeling a nerve burst. Like, as if I could feel the tendrils of the end of a nerve. It would just light up once and stop. Then light up and stop. It had stopped by the time I went to bed.   I worked out and had no issues. I haven't had any more spinal cord issues. I went to my scheduled accupuncture appointment today and it settled some of what was still in my hands. I worked all day as well in retail with no issues. I haven't had any more issues with the "heavy feeling" and my lumbar region was fine by bedtime. My feet are fine now. I am having nerve issues now but it's hard to say if it's my normal issues or still aggravated by the vaccine.   I'm having zero flu symptoms or anything from the vaccine they reported I may have. My arm at the injection site has no welt, redness, I can't find it, and is sore but it's like being hit by a softball. On the pain scale I'm used to: it's a 1/10.   I really do live with horrid chronic pain now.
LAB_DATA: I will be calling my neurologist Dr. I have not yet.
OTHER_MEDS: gabapentin (400mg/day); baclofen (30mg/day); neomycin and polymyxin B sulfates and dexamethasone ophthlamic soln; timolol maleate opthalmic soln; sodium divalproex er (750mg/day); glucosamin chondroitin; zinc; calcium; vitamin D; gingko sma

suffers from asthma but never had the symptoms she's had now; shortness of breath; hoarse/ hoarseness; audible wheezing; doesn't have the energy; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable nurse (patient). This 84-year-old female patient received bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE), dose 2 via an unspecified route of administration, administered in Arm Left on 18Mar2021 10:00 (Batch/Lot Number: EN6208) as 0.3 ml, single for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included asthma from 2019 and ongoing, when she would sleep her oxygen would drop, and shrunk from 5 feet 5 1/4 inches to now 5 feet 2 inches. She never found out why her oxygen saturations dropped at night but she does not have sleep apnea. Her saturations would drop down to the 80s and she would still be sleeping. Concomitant medications included ongoing albuterol [salbutamol] taken for asthma and oxygen taken for "when she would sleep her oxygen would drop" from 2012 and ongoing. Patient previously took Anoro and Qvar in Aug2019. Patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 on 25Feb2021 (lot number: EN6206, NDC:59267-1000-01, Expiry date unknown) in the left arm. With the first vaccine she did not have any symptoms, she thought she got saline. Only symptoms she felt were when they told her to wait 15 minutes and she sat there and when she got up and she was driving and had her window down her nose felt like it was swelling. She lost her sense of smell due to an injury and she had an acute sense of smell of tobacco from the car next to her. That is the only symptom she had. The acute sense of smell was about 30 minutes after she got her injection, about 5-7 minutes after that. She left about 10:30 am and it happened around 10:35-10:37 am. The acute sense of smell was short lived, it happened for a minute or two. Several years ago she had shoulder surgery and had her great granddaughter and she was playing with her and her foot got caught in the coffee table and she fell and her nose got cut and lost her sense of smell. When asked for seriousness criteria, patient stated it was significant because she had not been able to smell since 2011 and she had the sensation of her nose swelling. She felt like that but she was driving and could not look at her nose. She didn't have the feeling 15 minutes after the vaccine, she had been driving for 5-7 minutes and had the feeling and it was exactly when she got in the car. It was significant because she was able to smell something. Patient had her second dose of the Pfizer Covid-19 vaccine on 18Mar2021 and had shortness of breath. She suffers from asthma but never had the symptoms she's had now. She did not seem to be getting better and the slightest movement, she's short of breath. She is taking the medicine that she normally takes but never had to take it this much. She was short of breath and not paying that much attention to it, when she goes out she wears a mask, since last year, and she went to put the trash out and had shortness of breath stepping out the back door. She was talking to a friend long distance and she told her she was so short of breath. To get out of bed and turn in bed she's more short of breath. The shortness of breath may have started before Friday 26Mar2021 but that's when she noticed it. She would have her mask on, park her car and go to the post office and when she would walk to her PO box, which is the first of the boxes, she was exhausted and not getting enough air and she noticed it. But then when she went outside to put the trash out, just a step outside she was short of breath, that's when she began to notice. She has never been this short of breath and her breathing and exchange of air has never been this bad. She thought she would maybe get her smell back and in all the years she's been diagnosed with asthma she's never had the wheezing and shortness of breath that she's had now. She's never heard herself wheeze. Monday night she was up at 3 am and got up to go to the bathroom and she was so short of breath. She had to take it at 3:30 am and that had never happened to her. She never had wheezing until the second vaccine. She doesn't need a stethoscope to hear the wheezing and that most people have asthma with wheezing but she did not. Patient was not taking the Qvar until after the second dose of the vaccine and was only using the albuterol before. She would take two puffs in her car and then put two masks before getting out. No additional vaccines administered on same date of the Pfizer suspect. No AE required a visit to emergency room or physician office. She was scheduled to see her primary doctor on 13Apr2021 but could not get in earlier and attempted to see her pulmonary doctor and the earliest she can is 07Apr2021 and she has that appointment. Patient was also very hoarse. From time to time medications like her inhaler for her asthma sometimes makes her hoarse. This time she has the hoarseness even when she doesn't take her inhaler. She has audible wheezing. She would not consider the shortness of breath life threatening but it is concerning because she is not able to do what she needs to do because she doesn't have the energy. Hoarseness is worsening because she is taking more of the medications she's normally taking and now she is taking the inhaler twice a day because she is more short of breath. The one inhaler she is using is Qvar. She has been taking the albuterol more also. Hoarseness is not life threatening, it is effective but it is not disabling. The more she talks, the more hoarse she gets. Relatedness of drug to reactions shortness of breath, very hoarse, by primary source reporter (Method of assessment: Global Introspection) was related.
